SDSS J0100 + 2802 ( SDSS J010013.02 + 280225.8 ) is a hyperluminous quasar located near the border of the constellations Pisces and Andromeda .

Chi Herculis ( χ Her ) is a star in the constellation Hercules .
HD 73534 is an 8th magnitude G - type subgiant star located approximately 260 light years away in the constellation Cancer .
HD 149026 , also named Ogma , is a yellow subgiant star approximately 260 light - years from the Sun in the constellation of Hercules .
75 Cancri ( abbr . : 75 Cnc ) is a spectroscopic binary star in the constellation Cancer .
NGC 6152 is an open cluster of stars located in the constellation Norma .
IC 1613 ( also known as Caldwell 51 ) is an irregular dwarf galaxy in the constellation Cetus near the star 26 Ceti .
Mu Arietis ( μ Ari , μ Arietis ) is the Bayer designation for a star system in the northern constellation of Aries .
NGC 5170 is an edge - on spiral galaxy in the constellation Virgo .
WISE J222055.31−362817.4 ( designation abbreviated to WISE 2220−3628 ) is a brown dwarf of spectral class Y0 , located in constellation Grus at approximately 26 light - years from Earth .
The Crab Nebula ( catalogue designations M1 , NGC 1952 , Taurus A ) is a supernova remnant and pulsar wind nebula in the constellation of Taurus .
UY Scuti is a bright red supergiant and pulsating variable star in the constellation Scutum .
38 Geminorum ( 38 Gem ) is a star in the constellation Gemini .
TVLM513 - 46546 is an ultracool brown dwarf in the constellation Boötes , exhibiting a flare star activity and all the same varying semi - regularly due to dissimilarly bright hemispheres and a rotation period of about two days .
13 Monocerotis ( 13 Mon ) is a supergiant star in the constellation Monoceros .
HD 41742/41700 is a star system that lies approximately 87 light - years away in the constellation of Puppis .
18 Ursae Majoris ( 18 UMa ) is a star in the constellation Ursa Major .
HD 2767 is a double star located 116 parsecs ( 380 ly ) away in the constellation Andromeda .
NGC 82 is a magnitude 14.8 star located in the Andromeda constellation .
HD 125823 , also known as V761 Centauri and a Centauri , is a star in the constellation Centaurus .
WR 7 or HD 56925/HIP 35 378 is a Wolf - Rayet star at the centre of the nebula NGC 2359 ( also known as the Thor 's Helmet Nebula ) in the constellation of Canis Major .
Messier 89 ( M89 for short , also known as NGC 4552 ) is an elliptical galaxy in the constellation Virgo .
WASP-13 is a star in the Lynx constellation .
Kepler-46 , previously designated KOI-872 , is a star located in the constellation Lyra .
NGC 5929 is a Seyfert galaxy in the constellation Boötes .
NGC 265 is an open cluster in the Small Magellanic Cloud , which is located in the constellation Tucana .
Alpha Comae Berenices ( Alpha Com , α Com , α Comae Berenices ) is a star in the constellation Coma Berenices ( Berenice 's Hair ) .

72 Cygni ( 72 Cyg ) is a star in the constellation Cygnus .
2MASS J15074769 - 1627386 ( also abbreviated to 2MASS 1507 - 1627 ) is a brown dwarf in the constellation Libra , located about 23.9 light - years from Earth .

HD 179821 is a yellow supergiant star in the constellation of Aquila , surrounded by a detached dust shell .
HD 43691 is a G - type star with magnitude + 8.03 located approximately 260 light - years away in the constellation Auriga .
HD 166 or V439 Andromedae ( ADS 69 A ) is a 6th magnitude star in the constellation Andromeda , approximately 45 light years away from Earth .
HD 212771 b is an extrasolar planet orbiting the G - type star HD 212771 approximately 427 light years away in the constellation Aquarius .
R Horologii ( also known as HD 18242 ) is a red giant star approximately 100 light - years away in the constellation Horologium .
11 Arietis ( abbreviated 11 Ari ) is a star in the northern constellation of Aries .
WISE 2056 + 1459 ( full designation WISEPC J205628.90 + 145953.3 ) is a brown dwarf of spectral class Y0 , located in constellation Delphinus at approximately 23.3 light - years from Earth .
HD 101930 is a dim 8th magnitude star located approximately 95 light years away in the constellation of Centaurus .
26 Ursae Majoris ( 26 UMa ) is a star in the constellation Ursa Major .
NGC 4534 is a spiral galaxy , located in the Canes Venatici constellation .
NGC 4535 is a barred spiral galaxy located some 54 million light years from Earth in the constellation Virgo .
48 Persei ( also known as c Persei , 48 Per , HR 1273 , HIP 19343 , or HD 25940 ) is a Be star in the constellation Perseus , approximately the 500th brightest of the visible stars in apparent magnitude .
Eta Ceti ( η Cet , η Ceti ) is a star in the equatorial constellation of Cetus , the whale .
Kappa Piscium ( Kappa Psc , κ Piscium , κ Psc ) is a multiple star approximately 162 light years away from Earth , in the constellation Pisces .
Messier 47 ( Messier Object 47 , M47 , or NGC 2422 ) is an open cluster in the constellation Puppis .
HD 159868 is a yellow dwarf star approximately 172 light - years away in the constellation of Scorpius .
Groves Island is an ice - covered island 9 kilometres ( 5 nmi ) long , lying close off the coast of Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica , between Siemiatkowski Glacier and Land Glacier .
Ninnis Glacier ( 68 ° 22′S 147 ° 0′E ) is a large , heavily hummocked and crevassed glacier descending steeply from the high interior to the sea in a broad valley , on George V Coast in Antarctica .
Larsen Glacier ( 75 ° 6′S 162 ° 28′E ) is a glacier flowing southeast from Reeves Neve , through the Prince Albert Mountains and entering the Ross Sea just south of Mount Crummer in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Wilkins Sound is a seaway in Antarctica that is largely occupied by the Wilkins Ice Shelf .
Asen Peak ( Asenov Vrah \a-'se - nov ' vr&h\ ) is a peak in eastern Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Boyce Ridge is a 4.4-mile ( 7-km ) ridge that extends westward from Taylor Ledge to the head of Nimitz Glacier in Sentinel Range , Ellsworth Mountains in Antarctica .
Låvebrua Island is an island , 95 metres ( 310 ft ) high , lying 1.3 kilometres ( 0.7 nmi ) east of South Point , Deception Island , in the South Shetland Islands off Antarctica .
Gangapur Dam is on the river Godavari near Gangawadi village and is Asia 's largest earthen dam , Nashik .
Marshall Nunatak ( 74 ° 10′S 75 ° 41′W ) is a somewhat isolated rock nunatak , 23 nautical miles ( 43 km ) east - southeast of the FitzGerald Bluffs in Ellsworth Land , Antarctica .
Scarlatti Peak ( 71 ° 16′S 70 ° 26′W ) is a conspicuous pyramidal peak , rising to 750 m , 8 nautical miles ( 15 km ) northwest of Holst Peak and 12 nautical miles ( 22 km ) east of Walton Mountains in the central part of Alexander Island , Antarctica .
The Medina Peaks ( 85 ° 36′S 155 ° 54′W ) are rugged , mainly ice - free , peaks surmounting a ridge 15 nautical miles ( 28 km ) long , extending north along the east side of Goodale Glacier to the edge of the Ross Ice Shelf , Antarctica .
Gauss Glacier ( 77 ° 58′S 163 ° 44′E ) is a steep glacier on the north side of Datum Peak , descending west from the southwestern extremity of Hobbs Ridge into Blue Glacier , in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Harrop Island is a small island lying close to the coast and 6 kilometres ( 3 nmi ) northwest of Felton Head , Enderby Land , Antarctica .
Nedelya Point ( Bulgarian : нос Неделя , `` Nos Nedelya '' \'nos ne-'de - lya\ ) is a sharp ice - free point on the north coast of Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica projecting 300 m into Barclay Bay .
Host Island ( 64 ° 56′S 63 ° 55′W ) is an island lying immediately southeast of Manciple Island in the Wauwermans Islands , in the Wilhelm Archipelago , Antarctica .
Gerontius Glacier ( 69 ° 31′S 70 ° 34′W ) is a glacier flowing north from the Elgar Uplands into Tufts Pass in northern Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Kaloyanov Peak ( Bulgarian : Калоянов връх , `` Kaloyanov Vrah '' \ka - lo-'ya - nov ' vr&h\ ) is the rocky , partly ice - free peak rising to 550 m in southeastern Poibrene Heights on Blagoevgrad Peninsula , Oscar II Coast , Graham Land in Antarctica .
' Mautino Peak ' is a peak at the west side of Packard Glacier in the Saint Johns Range of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Gin Cove ( 64 ° 3′S 58 ° 25′W ) is a cove in Antarctica indenting the northwest coast of James Ross Island to the north of Tumbledown Cliffs .
The Harvey Nunataks ( 66 ° 58′S 52 ° 0′E ) are four nunataks standing 4 nautical miles ( 7 km ) west of Mount Ryder , in the eastern part of the Tula Mountains in Enderby Land , Antarctica .
Pirogov Glacier ( Bulgarian : Пирогов ледник , `` Pirogov Lednik '' \pi - ro-'gov ' led - nik\ ) is a 5 km long and 1.5 km wide glacier situated south of Djerassi Glacier , west of the head of Mackenzie Glacier and northwest of Balanstra Glacier on Brabant Island in the Palmer Archipelago , Antarctica .
Lützow - Holm Bay is a large bay , about 220 kilometres ( 120 nmi ) wide , indenting the coast of Queen Maud Land in Antarctica between Riiser - Larsen Peninsula and the coastal angle immediately east of the Flatvaer Islands .
Lewis Bay is a bay indenting the north coast of Ross Island , Antarctica , between Mount Bird and Cape Tennyson .
Kvitholten Hill ( 71 ° 49′S 5 ° 51′E ) is a snow - clad hill at the east side of Austreskorve Glacier , standing just south of Sagbladet Ridge in the Mühlig - Hofmann Mountains of Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
The Amazon rainforest ( Portuguese : Floresta Amazônica or Amazônia ; Spanish : Selva Amazónica , Amazonía or usually Amazonia ; French : Forêt amazonienne ; Dutch : Amazoneregenwoud ) , also known in English as Amazonia or the Amazon Jungle , is a moist broadleaf forest that covers most of the Amazon basin of South America .
Rennick Glacier is broad glacier , nearly 200 miles long , which is one of the largest in Antarctica .
Bhutan ( /buːˈtɑːn/ ; Dzongkha འབྲུག་ཡུལ Dru Ü , IPA : ( ʈʂɦu yː ) ) , officially the Kingdom of Bhutan , is a landlocked country in South Asia at the eastern end of the Himalayas .
Cape Henderson ( 66 ° 11′S 100 ° 44′E ) is an ice - free cape , overlain by morainic drift , marking the northwest end of the Bunger Hills in Antarctica .
France ( French : ( fʁɑ̃s ) ) , officially the French Republic ( French : République française ( ʁepyblik fʁɑ̃sɛz ) ) , is a sovereign state comprising territory in western Europe and several overseas regions and territories .
Halle Flat ( 76 ° 40′S 159 ° 50′E ) is a relatively flat area just southward of Coxcomb Peak in the Allan Hills of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Mount Flett ( 68 ° 9′S 49 ° 12′E ) is a mountain between Mount Marriner and Mount Underwood in the central Nye Mountains of Antarctica .
Jackson Pond is a freshwater frozen pond midway between the terminus of Wright Upper Glacier and Anvil Pond in the Labyrinth , McMurdo Dry Valleys , Antarctica .
Yoglav Crag ( Bulgarian : Йоглавски камък , `` Yoglavski Kamak '' \'yo - glav - ski ' ka - m&k\ ) is the rocky peak rising to 865 m in the south extremity of Kondofrey Heights on Trinity Peninsula in Graham Land , Antarctica .
Peter Peak ( Petrov Vrah \pe-'trov ' vr&h\ ) is an 850 m knob in Delchev Ridge , Tangra Mountains , eastern Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Besapara Hill ( Halm Besapara \'h&lm be - sa-'pa - ra\ ) is a hill of 250 m projecting from Sopot Ice Piedmont in Delchev Ridge , Tangra Mountains on Livingston Island , South Shetland Islands in Antarctica .
Iroquois Plateau ( 83 ° 51′S 54 ° 0′W ) is a large , mainly ice - covered plateau situated east of the southern part of the Washington Escarpment in the Pensacola Mountains of Edith Ronne Land , Antarctica .
Metchnikoff Point is a point forming the western extremity of Pasteur Peninsula in northern Brabant Island , in the Palmer Archipelago , Antarctica .
Mount Newman ( 69 ° 11′S 71 ° 26′W ) is a mountain rising to about 1,150 m in northeast Havre Mountains , north Alexander Island , Antarctica .
Plovdiv Peak ( Vrah Plovdiv \'vr&h ' plov - div\ ) is a peak rising to 1,040 m in the east extremity of Levski Ridge , Tangra Mountains , Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Francis Island is an island which is irregular in shape , 13 kilometres ( 7 nmi ) long and 9 kilometres ( 5 nmi ) wide , lying 22 kilometres ( 12 nmi ) east - northeast of Choyce Point , off the east coast of Graham Land , Antarctica .
Hjorth Hill ( 77 ° 31′S 163 ° 37′E ) is a rounded , ice - free mountain , 760 metres ( 2,500 ft ) high , standing just north of New Harbour and 2 nautical miles ( 4 km ) south of Hogback Hill , in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Marsh Ridge ( 85 ° 46′S 146 ° 10′W ) is a rocky ridge in Antarctica , 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) long .
Cherry Spur ( 72 ° 52′S 162 ° 0′E ) is a prominent rock spur that forms the southwest portion of Sculpture Mountain at the southern end of the Monument Nunataks , Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Henry Inlet is a narrow , ice - filled inlet about 12 nautical miles ( 22 km ) long , indenting the north coast of Thurston Island , Antarctica , immediately east of Hughes Peninsula .
Milan Ridge ( 83 ° 15′S 156 ° 8′E ) is a mainly ice - free ridge , 5 nautical miles ( 9 km ) long , bordering the west side of Ascent Glacier in the Miller Range , Antarctica .
The Kinzl Crests ( 67 ° 5′S 66 ° 18′W ) are three peaks , 2,135 metres ( 7,000 ft ) high , on Pernik Peninsula , Loubet Coast in Graham Land , Antarctica , standing 3 nautical miles ( 6 km ) east of Salmon Cove and Lallemand Fjord .
Lubbock Ridge ( 84 ° 52′S 175 ° 25′W ) is a high ridge in Antarctica , about 5 nautical miles ( 9 km ) long , extending west from Mount Wade and terminating in a steep bluff at the east side of Shackleton Glacier .
The Linnormen Hills ( 72 ° 4′S 14 ° 33′E ) are hills extending southwest -- northeast and rising close east of Skavlhø Mountain in the Payer Mountains of Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Mill Mountain ( 79 ° 26′S 157 ° 52′E ) is a large flat - topped mountain , 2,730 metres ( 8,960 ft ) high , forming the eastern end of Festive Plateau in the Cook Mountains of Antarctica .
Kenneth Ridge ( 70 ° 57′S 71 ° 30′E ) is the northernmost of three rock outcrops in the northern part of the Manning Nunataks , Antarctica .
Rymill Bay is a bay in Antarctica .
Washington Escarpment ( 83 ° 42′S 55 ° 8′W ) is the major west - facing escarpment of the Neptune Range , Pensacola Mountains in Antarctica , extending some 50 miles ( 80 km ) and being the point of origin of a number of west - trending rock ridges .
The Jigsaw Islands are two small islands lying off the southwest end of Wiencke Island , in the Palmer Archipelago , Antarctica .
Koltermann Peak ( 77 ° 29′S 160 ° 23′E ) is a peak rising to 2,166 metres ( 7,106 ft ) in the eastern part of the McAllister Hills , located west of the Olympus Range in Victoria Land , Antarctica .
The Heverley Nunataks ( 75 ° 33′S 128 ° 34′W ) are small , relatively isolated nunataks protruding through the ice 14 nautical miles ( 26 km ) northeast of the summit of Mount Flint in the McCuddin Mountains of Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Archer Point ( 69 ° 11′S 157 ° 39′E ) is a rocky headland on the coast marking the west side of Harald Bay , Antarctica .
Mount Cresswell is a domed , elongated mountain with a small conical peak at the west end , standing 25 nautical miles ( 46 km ) north - northeast of Mount Dummett in the southern Prince Charles Mountains of Antarctica .
Alberich Glacier ( 77 ° 36′S 161 ° 36′E ) is a small glacier that drains west from Junction Knob toward the east flank of Sykes Glacier , in the Asgard Range , Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Stellar Crests ( 71 ° 5′S 69 ° 15′W ) is a four prominent snow - covered peaks , rising to about 2,000 m , surmounting LeMay Range west of the north part of Planet Heights in central Alexander Island , Antarctica .
George Nunatak ( 85 ° 35′S 145 ° 26′W ) is a nunatak , 1,050 metres ( 3,440 ft ) high , located midway between the eastern part of the Harold Byrd Mountains and Leverett Glacier in Antarctica .
The Debelt Glacier ( Lednik Debelt \'led - nik ' de - belt\ ) on Varna Peninsula , Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica is situated southeast of Rose Valley Glacier and northeast of Panega Glacier .
Mayman Nunatak ( 71 ° 5′S 66 ° 56′E ) is a low rock outcrop , which has a domed appearance from the northeast , about 6 nautical miles ( 11 km ) southwest of Taylor Platform in the Prince Charles Mountains of Antarctica .
Flensing Icefall is a large icefall at the east side of the Bowers Mountains in Victoria Land , Antarctica , situated south of Platypus Ridge at the junction of Graveson Glacier and Rastorguev Glacier with Lillie Glacier .
Horseshoe Crater ( 78 ° 14′S 162 ° 53′E ) is a volcanic crater at the confluence of Radian Glacier and Pipecleaner Glacier in the Royal Society Range of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Granitnaya Mountain ( 72 ° 8′S 11 ° 38′E ) is a mountain , 2,880 metres ( 9,450 ft ) high , standing just east of Skeidshovden Mountain in the Wohlthat Mountains of Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Leningradskiy Island is an ice - covered island situated at the head of Leningradskiy Bay at the western margin of the Lazarev Ice Shelf , Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Mistral Ridge ( 69 ° 33′S 68 ° 4′W ) is a mostly snow - covered ridge extending 6 nautical miles ( 11 km ) in a northnorthwest -- southsoutheast direction , located 5 nautical miles ( 9 km ) east of Zonda Towers , Rymill Coast , Palmer Land , Antarctica .
Serdica Peak ( Vrah Serdica \'vr&h ' ser - di - ka\ ) rises to approximately 1,200 m in Levski Ridge , Tangra Mountains , Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Cutler Stack is a sea stack extending 170 by 150 m ( 186 by 164 yd ) and rising to 16 m ( 52 ft ) , lying off Nedelya Point in the south of Barclay Bay , western Livingston Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Grinda Ridge ( 71 ° 56′S 4 ° 26′E ) is a rock ridge 1.5 nautical miles ( 3 km ) long , immediately north of Mount Grytoyr in the Mühlig - Hofmann Mountains of Queen Maud Land , Antarctica .
Lundström Knoll ( 80 ° 31′S 20 ° 25′W ) is a rock knoll rising to about 1,400 metres ( 4,600 ft ) to the northeast of the Chevreul Cliffs in Pioneers Escarpment , Shackleton Range , Antarctica .
The Geoffrey Hills ( 67 ° 37′S 48 ° 36′E ) are a group of hills at the west end of the Raggatt Mountains in Enderby Land , Antarctica .
Mount McCormick ( 77 ° 0′S 144 ° 26′W ) is a mountain 2 nautical miles ( 4 km ) southeast of Mount Ralph in the Ford Ranges of Marie Byrd Land , Antarctica .
Linnaeus Terrace is a rock terrace on the north side of Oliver Peak in the Asgard Range of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
The Rouse Islands or Rouse Rocks are a small group of islands in the eastern part of Holme Bay in Antarctica , fringing the coast of Mac Robertson Land close south of Welch Island .
Michigan Plateau ( 86 ° 8′S 133 ° 30′W ) is an undulating ice - covered plateau , 30 nautical miles ( 56 km ) long , which rises to 3,000 metres ( 10,000 ft ) at the western side of Reedy Glacier , Antarctica .
Lodge Rock is a low , snow - capped rock , less than 30 metres ( 100 ft ) high , between Barn Rock and Hayrick Island in the Terra Firma Islands , off the west coast of Graham Land , Antarctica .
The Austkampane Hills are a group of hills rising to 2,210 meters ( 7,250 ft ) , standing 5 miles ( 8 km ) north of Menipa Peak in the Sør Rondane Mountains of Antarctica .
Lind Glacier ( 65 ° 23′S 64 ° 1′W ) is a glacier flowing west from Alencar Peak into the southern part of Collins Bay , on the west coast of Kiev Peninsula in Graham Land , Antarctica .
Dirtbag Nunatak ( 85 ° 32′S 144 ° 52′W ) is a ridge - like nunatak rising to 940 metres ( 3,080 ft ) , 3.5 nautical miles ( 6 km ) south - southwest of Mount Manke , in the Harold Byrd Mountains in Antarctica .
The Diversion Hills ( 73 ° 9′S 163 ° 30′E ) are a small group of low rock outcrops at the east extremity of Pain Mesa , in Victoria Land , Antarctica .

Radko Knoll ( Bulgarian : Радкова Могила , `` Radkova Mogila '' \'rad - ko - va mo-'gi - la\ ) is a rocky hill rising to 102 m on the north coast of Smyadovo Cove in the northwest of Rugged Island in the South Shetland Islands , Antarctica .
Pryor Peak is a peak rising at the west side of Giants Cirque in the Tyndall Mountains , Arrowsmith Peninsula , Loubet Coast , Antarctica .
Mount Coman ( 73 ° 49′S 64 ° 18′W ) is a prominent isolated mountain which rises above the ice - covered plateau of Palmer Land , located just westward of the Playfair Mountains in Antarctica .
Mars Hills ( 76 ° 40′S 162 ° 0′E ) are a small group of low rounded hills of a distinct red color , located 2.5 nautical miles ( 5 km ) north of Mount Davidson in the Convoy Range of Victoria Land , Antarctica .
Operation Deep Freeze ( OpDFrz or ODF ) is the codename for a series of United States missions to Antarctica , beginning with `` Operation Deep Freeze I '' in 1955 - -56 , followed by `` Operation Deep Freeze II '' , `` Operation Deep Freeze III '' , and so on .
The Fremouw Formation is a Triassic - age rock formation in the Transantarctic Mountains of Antarctica .
Morelli Glacier ( 72 ° 59′S 102 ° 38′W ) is a glacier in the western part of King Peninsula , Antarctica , 18 nautical miles ( 33 km ) southeast of Cape Waite , draining northeast to Abbot Ice Shelf in Peacock Sound .
Lemasters Bluff ( 73 ° 20′S 162 ° 12′E ) is a rock bluff at the eastern extremity of the Lichen Hills in Victoria Land , Antarctica .

Mill Stream Glacier ( 85 ° 20′S 171 ° 0′E ) is a tributary glacier , about 10 nautical miles ( 19 km ) wide , flowing west between the Supporters Range and Otway Massif in Antarctica to enter Mill Glacier .

Swob Sjaarda ( 1435 - 1520 ) was a Dutch noble , daughter of Douwe Tjaerts Aylva and Sjaarda Edwert and from 1455 married to Jarich Epes Hottinga .

St. George Littledale was born on 8 December 1851 , in Liverpool to Thomas Littledale and Julia Royds .

Judith Herzfeld ( born 12 January 1948 ) is Professor of Biophysical Chemistry at Brandeis University .
Jack Delano ( August 1 , 1914 -- August 12 , 1997 ) was an American photographer for the Farm Security Administration ( FSA ) and a composer noted for his use of Puerto Rican folk material .

Jonathan Sessler ( born 20 May 1956 in Urbana , Illinois ) is a professor of chemistry at The University of Texas at Austin .

Dorsey Armstrong ( born 1970 ) is Associate Professor of English and Medieval Literature at Purdue University .

Ahmed Fareed is a studio host and reporter for American TV channel Comcast SportsNet Bay Area .
Prof . Charles Spence is an experimental psychologist at the University of Oxford .

Christen Jensen ( 1881 - -1961 ) was an American educator who twice served as interim president of Brigham Young University ( BYU ) .
Torsten Sjögren was professor of psychiatry at Karolinska Institutet from 1945 to 1961 .
Thomas S. Lundgren is an American fluid dynamicist and Professor Emeritus of Aerospace Engineering and Mechanics at the University of Minnesota He is known for his work in the field of theoretical fluid dynamics .
François Grosjean is a Professor Emeritus and former Director of the Language and Speech Processing Laboratory at the University of Neuchâtel ( Switzerland ) .
Vijay P. Parashar , BDS , MDS , DDS , is an Oral and Maxillofacial Radiologist currently working as Faculty at Midwestern University , Glendale , AZ .
Vernon Benjamin Mountcastle ( July 15 , 1918 -- January 11 , 2015 ) was Professor Emeritus of Neuroscience at Johns Hopkins University .
Robert H. Brower ( 23 March 1923 -- 29 February 1988 ) was a Professor of Far East Language and Literature , Japanese Language and Literature , Chair of Far East Language and Literature at the University of Michigan from 1966 to 1988 .
Julie Larson - Green ( born 1962 ) is the Chief Experience Officer of Microsoft 's `` My Life & Work '' team at Microsoft , where she has worked since 1993 .
George Casella ( January 22 , 1951 -- June 17 , 2012 ) was a Distinguished Professor in the Department of Statistics at the University of Florida .
Hartley Rogers , Jr. was a mathematician who worked in recursion theory , and was a professor in the Mathematics Department of the Massachusetts Institute of Technology .
Arne Johan Vetlesen ( born 10 September 1960 ) is a Norwegian professor of philosophy at the University of Oslo , who concentrates on the topic of ethics and social philosophy .
Arthur Oliver Wheeler ( May 1 , 1860 -- May 20 , 1945 ) was born in Ireland and immigrated to Canada in 1876 at the age of 16 .
Pietro De Camilli is an Italian - American biologist and John Klingenstein Professor of Neuroscience and Cell Biology at Yale University School of Medicine .
Mike Harrington is the co - founder of the computer game development company , Valve Corporation .
Dr. John T. James is the Chief Toxicologist for the National Aeronautics & Space Administration .
John Spotton ( January 1 , 1927 - March 3 , 1991 ) was a Canadian filmmaker with the National Film Board of Canada .
Sanjiv M. Ravi Kanbur ( born 28 August 1954 ) , is T.H. Lee Professor of World Affairs , International Professor of Applied Economics , and Professor of Economics at Cornell University .
Omeljan Pritsak ( Ukrainian : Омеля́н Пріца́к ; 7 April 1919 , Luka , Sambir County , Austrian Galicia -- 29 May 2006 , Boston , Massachusetts , U.S. ) was the first Mykhailo Hrushevsky Professor of Ukrainian History at Harvard University and the founder and first director ( 1973 - -1989 ) of the Harvard Ukrainian Research Institute .
Kazimierz Wyka ( 1910 - -1975 ) was a Polish literary historian , literary critic , and professor at the Jagiellonian University in Kraków .
Steven D. Eppinger ( born 1961 ) is an American engineer , and Professor of Management , Professor of Management Science and Innovation , and Professor of Engineering Systems at Massachusetts Institute of Technology , known for his work on product design and product development .
Adam B. Jaffe ( born May 1955 ) is Director of Motu Economic and Public Policy Research , in Wellington , New Zealand , and formerly a professor of Economics at Brandeis University .
Jeffrey A. Hutchings ( born 11 September 1958 ) is a Canadian - born fisheries scientist , a Faculty of Science Killam Professor of Biology , and former Canada Research Chair in Marine Conservation and Biodiversity ( 2002 - 2011 ) at Dalhousie University .
Ranjit Sondhi was a BBC Governor with responsibility for the English regions .
Jacob K. Olupona is a scholar of indigenous African religions who came to Harvard after serving as a professor at the University of California , Davis .
Muzaffar Alam ( born 3 February 1947 ) is the George V. Bobrinskoy Professor in South Asian Languages and Civilizations at the University of Chicago .
Evan Chambers ( born 1963 , Alexandria , Louisiana ) is a composer , traditional Irish fiddler , and Professor of Composition at the University of Michigan .

Charles Louis Auguste Jacques Seydoux ( 1870 - -1929 ) was a French diplomat , economist and Director of Commercial Relations at the French Foreign Ministry .

Ernst Gottlieb Baron or Ernst Theofil Baron ( 17 February 1696 -- 12 April 1760 ) , was a German lutenist , composer and writer on music .

In mathematics , Chebyshev 's sum inequality , named after Pafnuty Chebyshev , states that if a_1 \geq a_2 \geq \cdots \geq a_n and b_1 \geq b_2 \geq \cdots \geq b_n , then ( 1\over n ) \sum--(k=1)^n a_k \cdot b_k \geq \left((1\over n)\sum--(k=1)^n a_k\right)\left((1\over n)\sum--(k=1)^n b_k\right ) .
In an economy , the consumption of Veblen goods is a function of the Veblen effect ( goods desired for being over - priced ) that is named after the American economist Thorstein Veblen , who first identified conspicuous consumption as a mode of status - seeking in The Theory of the Leisure Class ( 1899 ) .

Mike Bernier ( born 1968 ) is a Canadian politician , who was elected to the Legislative Assembly of British Columbia in the 2013 provincial election .

Jonkheer Petrus Andreas van Meeuwen ( ' s - Hertogenbosch , January 27 , 1772 -- Maastricht , August 19 , 1848 ) was a Dutch politician , lawyer , a member of the House of Representatives of the Netherlands , and a member of the Council of State of the Netherlands .
Gaspard Fauteux , PC ( August 27 , 1898 -- March 29 , 1963 ) was a Canadian parliamentarian , Speaker of the Canadian House of Commons ( 1945 - -1949 ) , and the 19th Lieutenant Governor of Quebec ( 1950 - -1958 ) .
Laimdota Straujuma ( born 24 February 1951 ) is a Latvian economist who was the Prime Minister of Latvia from January 2014 to February 2016 .
Joseph Raphael John Crimont , SJ ( February 2 , 1858 -- May 20 , 1945 ) was a 20th - century bishop in the Catholic Church in the United States .
Dr. Paul Martin Pearson ( October 22 , 1871 -- March 26 , 1938 ) was an author , college professor , and a very embattled first civilian Governor of the United States Virgin Islands .
Stefano Pignatelli ( Perugia , 1578 -- Rome , 12 August 1623 ) was an Italian cardinal .
Giovanni Vincenzo Gonzaga ( 1540 - -1591 ) was an Italian Roman Catholic cardinal .
In 1945 Robert Neddermeyer served briefly as the mayor of Liebenwalde , the town near to which he still owned a small chicken farm .
Sherri Smith Buffington , formerly Sherri Smith Cheek ( born August 1966 ) , is a businesswoman from Shreveport , Louisiana , who is a third - term Republican member of the Louisiana State Senate for District 38 ( south Caddo and DeSoto parishes ) .
Sheila Fraser ( born September 16 , 1950 ) served as Auditor General of Canada from 2001 to 2011 .
Dušan Vujović ( Serbian Cyrillic : Душан Вујовић ; born 22 July 1951 ) is a Serbian politician and current Minister of Finance in the Government of Serbia .
Andrew Messenger ( 1650 -- October 1730 ) was a deputy of the General Assembly of the Colony of Connecticut from Norwalk in the sessions of May 1691 , and October 1696 , and a member of the Connecticut House of Representatives in the sessions of October 1700 , October 1701 , and May 1702 .
Jim Ardis is the mayor of Peoria , Illinois , a position he has held since 2005 .
Richard Bélisle ( born 20 July 1946 in Montreal , Quebec ) is a Canadian politician who was a member of the House of Commons of Canada from 1993 to 1997 .
Flavius Odoacer ( 433 - -493 ) , also known as Flavius Odovacer ( Italian : Odoacre , Latin : Odoacerus German : Odoaker ) , was a soldier who in 476 became the first King of Italy ( 476 - -493 ) .
Sofu Mehmed Pasha ( died August 1649 ) , also known as Mevlevi Mehmed Pasha , was an Ottoman statesman who served as grand vizier and defterdar ( finance minister ) .
Raffaele Forni ( Villa Bedretto , 24 May 1906 -- Lugano , 29 September 1990 ) was a Roman Catholic archbishop .
Frederick de la Roche ( died 30 October 1174 ) was the sixth Latin archbishop of Tyre ( 1164 - -1174 ) , chancellor of the kingdom of Jerusalem ( c. 1150 ) , and the chief diplomat of King Amalric I. He was a Lorrainer , from the town of La Roche , of noble stock .
Sir Otto Jaffe , JP ( born 13 August 1846 , Hamburg -- died 29 April 1929 , London ) was a German - born Jewish businessman , who was twice elected Lord Mayor of Belfast .

Roger - Émile Aubry , C.Ss . R. , ( 11 April 1923 -- 17 February 2010 ) was the Roman Catholic bishop of the Vicariate Apostolic of Reyes , Bolivia .
Cecil L. Collins ( April 21 , 1926 -- September 30 , 2007 ) is the former Mayor of North Augusta , South Carolina , U.S. , from 1967 to 1971 and a member of the South Carolina House of Representatives from 1972 to 1977 .
Rudolf Kirchschläger ( 20 March 1915 -- 30 March 2000 ) was an Austrian diplomat , politician , judge and , from 1974 to 1986 , the eighth President of Austria .
Tadeusz Paweł Zakrzewski ( 11 August 1883 in Skoki -- 26 November 1961 ) was a Polish Catholic priest , auxiliary bishop of Łomża ( 1938 - -1946 ) , bishop of Płock ( 1946 - -1961 ) , rector of Polish Papal Institute in Rome ( 1928 - -1938 ) .
Ioannis Kolokotronis ( Greek : Ιωάνης Κολοκοτρώνης ; 1805 - 1868 ) , or Gennaios Kolokotronis ( Greek : Γενναίος Κολοκοτρώνης ) as the other were calling him was a Greek warrior of the Greek War of Independence , general and Prime Minister of Greece .

Abner Coburn ( March 22 , 1803 -- January 4 , 1885 ) was the 30th Governor of Maine from 1863 to 1864 and a prominent individual in Skowhegan , Maine until his death .

Alexandru G. Golescu ( 1819 -- 15 August 1881 ) was a Romanian politician who served as a Prime Minister of Romania in 1870 ( between 14 February and 1 May ) .
Ron Suster is a former member of the Ohio House of Representatives , and a current judge in Cuyahoga County .

John Henry Kinkead ( December 10 , 1826 -- August 15 , 1904 ) was an American businessman and politician who served as the third Governor of Nevada and the first Governor of the District of Alaska .
Blessed Andrea Carlo Ferrari ( 13 August 1850 -- 2 February 1921 ) was an Italian cardinal of the Roman Catholic Church who served as the Archbishop of Milan .

Larry Galizio ( born 1964 ) was a Democratic member of the Oregon House of Representatives , representing District 35 from 2004 to 2010 .
Charles de Ferriol ( 1652 - -1722 ) was a French ambassador sent by Louis XIV to the Ottoman Empire from 1692 to 1711 , during the rule of Sultan Ahmed III . A painting by Jean - Baptiste van Mour , who had accompanied him on his mission to Constantinople , shows his reception by the Sultan .

The Next Day is the twenty - fourth studio album by English musician David Bowie , released on 8 March 2013 on his ISO Records label , under exclusive licence to Columbia Records .

Murnau 's seminal silent film Nosferatu , eine Symphonie des Grauens ( 1922 ) , which differs somewhat from Stoker 's original work .

The Basketball League Belgium ( BLB ) Division I , for sponsorship reasons , known as the Scooore League , is the highest tier professional basketball league in Belgium .
The New York City Marathon ( branded TCS New York City Marathon and formerly branded ING New York City Marathon for sponsorship reasons ) is an annual marathon ( 42.195 km or 26.219 mi ) that courses through the five boroughs of New York City .
John Wisden ( 5 September 1826 -- 5 April 1884 ) was an English cricketer who played 187 first - class cricket matches for three English county cricket teams , Kent , Middlesex and Sussex .
SV Babelsberg 03 is a German association football club based in Potsdam - Babelsberg , on the outskirts of Berlin .
Swamp football ( sometimes called Swamp soccer ) is a form of association football that is played in bogs or swamps .

Scott Franklin ( born 23 August 1980 in Regina , Saskatchewan , Canada ) , is a Canadian rugby union player who plays rugby for the Prairie Wolf Pack in Canada , and for the Canadian national team .
Deyonta Davis ( born December 2 , 1996 ) is an American basketball player who currently attends Michigan State University in East Lansing , Michigan .
Dacryodes is a genus of about 60 species of trees in the family Burseraceae .
Phoradendron libocedri is a species of flowering plant in the sandalwood family known by the common name incense - cedar mistletoe .
Ecsenius axelrodi , known commonly as the Axelrod 's clown blenny or the Axelrod 's combtooth blenny , is a species of ray - finned fish in the family Blenniidae , the combtooth blennies .
It contains only one species , Ptychotheca pallidivirens , which is found in New Guinea .
Leptosiphon rattanii ( syn . Linanthus rattanii ) is a rare species of flowering plant in the phlox family known by the common name Rattan 's linanthus .
Fucus virsoides is a species of brown alga endemic to the Adriatic Sea .
Aerides falcata is a species of epiphytic orchid native to Yunnan , Vietnam , Thailand , Laos , Cambodia , Myanmar .
Placospermum is a genus of a single species of large trees , constituting part of the plant family Proteaceae .
Amapanesia exotica is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Amapanesia .
Cornus alternifolia is a species of flowering plant in the dogwood family Cornaceae , native to eastern North America , from Newfoundland west to southern Manitoba and Minnesota , and south to northern Florida and Mississippi .
Colliguaja odorifera is a lignotuberous species of the family Euphorbiaceae .
Phyllonotus globosus , common name : the Globular Apple Murex , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Chelotriton is an extinct genus of prehistoric salamanders that lived in Europe during the Middle Miocene .
Sarcococca zeylanica is a species of evergreen shrub or groundcover , endemic to Sri Lanka .
Geum montanum , Alpine avens , is a flowering plant species native to Europe .
Uncancylus foncki is a species of small , freshwater , air - breathing limpet , an aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusc in the family Planorbidae , the ram 's horn snails and their allies .
Tor douronensis , also known as Labeobarbus douronensis is a species of ray - finned fish of the family Cyprinidae in the genus Tor .
Aristolochia stevensii is a plant species native to northwestern Nicaragua and southwestern Honduras .
Epilobium densiflorum is a species of willowherb known by the common names denseflower willowherb , dense spike - primrose or dense boisduvalia .
Burmeistera is a genus of flowering plants in the bellflower family , Campanulaceae .
Calamagrostis bolanderi is a species of grass known by the common name Bolander 's reedgrass .
Tylopilus is a genus of over 100 species of mycorrhizal bolete fungi separated from Boletus .
Dromaius is a genus of ratite present in Australia .
Penicillium udagawae is an anamorph species of the genus of Penicillium .
Pantodonta is an extinct suborder ( or , according to some , an order ) of eutherian mammals .
It is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Ambivina filobasidia , described by B. Katz in 1974 .
Ferula tingitana ( the giant Tangier fennel ) is a species of the Apiaceae genus Ferula .
The Parabrotulidae , the false brotulas , are a small family of bathypelagic cusk eels that currently contains two genera .
Emarcusia morroensis , common name Morro Bay Aeolid , is a species of sea slug , specifically an aeolid nudibranch .
Galiteuthis phyllura , also known as the cockatoo squid , is a species of glass squid , possibly the largest in the genus .
Cephalotes is a Neotropical genus of tree - dwelling ant species , commonly known as turtle ants .
Pycnodus ( from Greek for crowded teeth ) is an extinct genus of ray - finned fish ranging from the Cretaceous to Eocene periods .
Parawenzichthys is an extinct genus of protacanthopterygian fish containing the single species Parawenzichthys minor , known from the Turonian age of present - day southern Brazil .
Streptanthus drepanoides is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name sicklefruit jewelflower .
Ciclospermum leptophyllum ( also , Cyclospermum l. ) is a species of plant in the celery family known by the common names marsh parsley , slender celery and fir - leaved celery .
Scleria terrestris is a species of flowering plant in the family Cyperaceae , the sedges .
Antalis is a genus of tusk shells , marine scaphopod mollusks .
Lyratoherpia is a genus of pholidoskepian solenogasters , shell - less , worm - like , marinemollusks .
Orya barbarica is a species of centipedes belonging to the family Oryidae .
Anthaenantiopsis is a genus of South American plants in the grass family .
Asterophora is a genus of fungi that grow as parasites on mushrooms .
Amsinckia lunaris is an uncommon species of fiddleneck known by the common name bent - flowered fiddleneck .
Eupholus geoffroyi is a species of beetles belonging to the family Curculionidae .
Neolecta is a genus of ascomycetous fungi that have fruiting bodies in the shape of unbranched to lobed bright yellowish , orangish to pale yellow - green colored , club - shaped , smooth , fleshy columns up to about 7 cm tall .
Portunidae is a family of crabs which contains the swimming crabs .
Microviridae is a family of bacteriophages with a single - stranded DNA genome .
Haliotis clathrata , common name the lovely abalone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Haliotidae , the abalones .
Paulchoffatiidae is a family of extinct mammals that lived predominantly during the Upper Jurassic period , though a couple of genera are known from the earliest Cretaceous .
Meligramma triangulifera is a European species of hoverfly .
The Camallanida are an order of nematodes .
Trictenotoma grayi is a species of beetle and the only representative of the family Trictenotomidae from southern India .
Haplochromis xenostoma was a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Victoria though it may be extinct .
Aspidites is a genus of pythons endemic to Australia .
Campanile auvertianum is a species of fossil sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Campanilidae .
Nebria rubicunda rubicunda is a subspecies of brown coloured ground beetle in the Nebriinae subfamily that can be found in Algeria , Morocco , Tunisia , and Spain .
Leuciscus dzungaricus is a species of cyprinid fish , known from Bulgan Gol river in Mongolia .
Procambarus fitzpatricki , sometimes called the spinytail crayfish , is a species of crayfish in the family Cambaridae .
Raorchestes longchuanensis ( Longchuan bubble - nest frog or Longchuan small treefrog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family .
Dorstenia appendiculata is a species of subshrub or herb in the plant family Moraceae which is native to eastern Brazil .
Afrotridactylus is a genus of pygmy mole crickets , which contains the following species :
Cypraea leucodon , common name the white - toothed cowry , is a rare cowry , a species of sea snail , or marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Brodiaea pallida is a rare species of flowering plant in the cluster - lily genus known by the common name Chinese Camp brodiaea .
Cyclamen coum , the eastern sowbread , is a species of flowering plant in the genus Cyclamen ( subgenus Gyrophoebe series Pubipedia ) .
Coryanthes alborosea is a species of Coryanthes ( bucket orchids ) found in Peru .
Bulbophyllum nigericum is an epiphytic or epilithic plant species in the Orchidaceae family .
Siphonochilus is a genus of plants native to sub - Saharan Africa .
Cariniana pyriformis ( known as Colombian Mahogany or Abarco ) is a species of woody plant in the Lecythidaceae family .
Buccinulum vittatum is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Buccinidae .
Choriolaus is a genus of beetles in the family Cerambycidae , containing the following species :

The Barred Carpet ( Martania taeniata ) is a species of moth of the Geometridae family .
Macrocystis is a genus of kelp ( large brown algae ) .
Emblemaria caldwelli , the Caribbean blenny , is a species of chaenopsid blenny found in coral reefs around the Bahamas , Belize , Honduras and Jamaica , in the western central Atlantic ocean .
Agastache mexicana is a species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name Mexican giant hyssop .
Baccharis glutinosa is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common names saltmarsh baccharis and Douglas ' falsewillow .
Chromocyphella is a genus of fungi in the family Chromocyphellaceae .
Ginebis crumpii , common name Crump 's margarite , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliotropidae .
Thoasia rugifrons is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Thoasia .
Clethra barbinervis is a species of flowering plant in the genus Clethra of the family Clethraceae , native to the far east , from eastern China , Korea , and Japan .
Ixodes brunneus is a species of tick in the genus Ixodes .
It is the sole species in the genus Terlinguachelys and is classified in the family Protostegidae along with other extinct marine turtles .
Alloteuthis africanus , also known as the African squid , is a species of squid in the family Loliginidae .
Holcoglossum is a genus of orchids , in the family Orchidaceae .
Anisomeles malabarica , with common name Malabar catmint , is a species of herbaceous plant native to India , Bangladesh , Sri Lanka , Andaman & Nicobar Islands , Thailand , Malaysia , Indonesia , New Guinea , Bismarck Archipelago , Mauritius , Réunion , northern Australia .
Sitticus finschi is a species of spider from Salticidae family , that can be found in Canada , Russia , and the United States .
Scalicus is a genus of armored searobins found in the Pacific and Indian Ocean .
Trypauchenopsis intermedia , the bearded eel goby , is a species of goby native to fresh waters from the Atlantic coast of South Africa to the Pacific island of Guam .
Colomesus psittacus , the Banded puffer , parrot puffer or South American estuarine puffer , is a species of pufferfish found all along the Western Atlantic coastline of South America from the Gulf of Paria down to the mouth of the Amazon River in Brazil .
Bulinus mutandensis is a species of freshwater gastropod in the Planorbidae family .
Before 1980 , Apis dorsata laboriosa was considered to be a subspecies of the widespread Apis dorsata , the giant honey bee , but in 1980 and for almost 20 years thereafter it was elevated to the rank of a separate species .
Danaideae is a tribe of flowering plants in the Rubiaceae family and contains about 50 species in 2 genera .
Mecomischus is a genus of North African flowering plants in the chamomile tribe within the daisy family .
Euonychophora is an order of Onychophoran representing all living onychophora .
Ruellia humilis ( wild petunia , fringeleaf wild petunia , hairy petunia , low wild petunia ) is a species of flowering plant in the Acanthaceae , the acanthus family .
Isonandra montana is plant species first described 1860 .
Platycrinitidae are an extinct family of Paleozoic stalked crinoids .
Polydectus cupulifer is a species of crab in the family Xanthidae , and the only species in the genus Polydectus .
Pseudophilautus simba ( Sinharaja shrub frog ) is a species of frog in the family Rhacophoridae endemic to Sri Lanka .
Pitcairnia angustifolia , the pina cortadora , is a species in the genus Pitcairnia .
The Garryales are a small order of dicotyledons , including only two families and three genera .
Megalorhipida dulcis is a species of moth in the genus Megalorhipida , known from Belize , Costa Rica , and Mexico .
Corydalus is a genus of large flying insects in the Corydalidae family , commonly known as dobsonflies .
Abies vejarii is a species of fir native to northeastern Mexico , in the states of Coahuila and Nuevo León , where it grows at high altitudes ( 2,000 - -3,300 m ) in the Sierra Madre Oriental .
Chaetodon pictus , the Horseshoe butterflyfish , is a species of butterflyfish found in the Red Sea , the Gulf of Aden and around Oman .
Spicara smaris , the picarel , is a species of ray - finned fish native to the eastern Atlantic Ocean , the Mediterranean Sea and the Black Sea .
Vanda ustii , the University of Santo Tomas ' vanda , is an orchid species found only in the Philippines .
Glipostena pelecotomoidea is a species of beetle in the Glipostena genus .
Hoploparia benedeni is a species of fossil lobster found in Cretaceous rocks in northern France .
Menippe adina is a species of crab , sometimes called the Gulf stone crab or Western Gulf stone crab .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Cornipulvina ellipsoides .
Ballerus is a genus of cyprinid fish containing two Eurasian species .
Laoterinaea flavovittata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Laoterinaea .
Phyllodytes is a genus of frogs ( heart - tongued frogs ) in the Hylidae family , found in eastern Brazil ( the species Phytotriades ( = Phyllodytes ) auratus from the island of Trinidad was previously considered a member of this genus ) .
Separatista helicoides is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Capulidae .
Plumeria pudica is a species of the genus Plumeria ( Apocynaceae ) , native to Panama , Colombia and Venezuela .
Euphorbia franckiana is a species of spurge native to southern Africa .
Aphroditeola is an agaric fungal genus that produces pink cantharelloid fruit bodies on coniferous forest floors .

Rubus corchorifolius is an Asian species of raspberry native to Korea , Japan , China , Vietnam , and Myanmar .
Forficulidae is a family of earwigs in the suborder Forficulina .
Centaurea diluta , the lesser star - thistle or North African knapweed , is a species of Centaurea .
Alcyonium palmatum or red dead man 's fingers is a species of soft coral in the Alcyoniidae family .

Ternstroemia bullata is a species of tree in the family Pentaphylacaceae .
Arctotis stoechadifolia , the African daisy or white arctotis , is a rare species of South African plants in the daisy family .
Farlowella curtirostra is a species of armored catfish native to the Lake Maracaibo drainage of Venezuela .
Hyaenodon ( `` hyena - toothed '' ) is the type genus of Hyaenodontidae , a group of extinct carnivorous fossil mammals from Eurasia , North America and Africa , with species existing temporally from the Eocene until the middle Miocene , existing for approximately 26.1 million years .
Gracixalus lumarius also known as the thorny tree frog is a species of rhacophorid frog discovered in 2014 that is native to Vietnam .
Zabrus balcanicus is a species of ground beetle in the Pelor subgenus that can be found in Bulgaria , Kosovo , Montenegro , Republic of Macedonia , Serbia , Voivodina and Turkey .
Nebria vseteckai is a species of ground beetle from Nebriinae subfamily that is endemic to Greece .
Parribacus is a genus of slipper lobsters , containing six species , all of which are used locally as human food sources .
Acusilas lepidus is a spider species in the genus Acusilas .
Philanthaxia pseudoaenea is a species of beetle that was discovered in Thailand on July , 2011 .
Lessemsaurus is an extinct genus of sauropodomorph dinosaur ( possibly a melanosaurid ) named for the writer of popular science books Don Lessem .
Glaucotes yuccivorus is a species of longhorn beetles of the subfamily Lamiinae , and the only species in the genus Glaucotes .
Agonum viridicupreum is a species of ground beetle in the Platyninae subfamily .
The Strepsiptera ( translation : `` twisted wing ' '' , giving rise to the insects ' common name , twisted - wing parasites ) are an endopterygote order of insects with nine extant families making up about 600 species .
Plagiobothrys scouleri is a common species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common name Scouler 's popcornflower and white forget - me - not .
Alophomyia is a genus of hymenopteran insects of the family Eulophidae .
Oreochromis variabilis , the Victoria tilapia , is a species of cichlid native to Lake Victoria and its tributaries , Lake Kyoga , Lake Kwania and Lake Salisbury as well as being found in the Victorian reach of the Nile above Murchison Falls .
Geranium sylvaticum ( wood cranesbill , woodland geranium ) is a species of hardy flowering plant in the Geraniaceae family , native to Europe and northern Turkey .
Hemicycla berkeleyi is a species of gastropod in the Helicidae family .
Acer spicatum ( mountain maple ) is a species of maple native to northeastern North America from Saskatchewan to Newfoundland , and south to Pennsylvania .
Passiflora vitifolia , the perfumed passionflower , is a species of Passiflora , native to southern Central America ( Costa Rica , Nicaragua , Panama ) and northwestern South America ( Venezuela , Colombia , Ecuador , Peru ) .
Gnathifera bidentella is a fringe - tufted moth species .
Ovula ovum , common name the common egg cowrie , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Ovulidae , the ovulids , cowry allies or false cowries .

Pachypodium lamerei is a species of Pachypodium .
The tribe Fabeae ( sometimes referred to as `` Vicieae '' ) is one of the subdivisions of the plant family Fabaceae .
Neoselachii are a grouping of cartilaginous fishes in subclass Elasmobranchii of class Chondrichthyes .
Scleromochlus ( Greek for `` hard fulcrum '' ) is an extinct genus of small avemetatarsalian from the Late Triassic period .
Scenedesmus is a genus of green algae , specifically of the Chlorophyceae .
Horkelia bolanderi is a rare species of flowering plant in the rose family known by the common names border horkelia and Bolander 's horkelia .
Xanthoparmelia tinctina is a species of lichen from the family Parmeliaceae that can be found in Arizona , California , Northern Africa and Europe .
Borisodon is an extinct genus of eutherians which existed in what is now Kazakhstan during the Turonian age .
The type and only known species is Tuarangisaurus keyesi .

Phyllopachyceras is an extinct genus of ammonoid cephalopods belonging to the family Phylloceratidae .
Woodhouse 's antpecker ( Parmoptila woodhousei ) is an unusual bird of uncertain affinities species of estrildid finch found in wetter land of Central Africa , its localized in the forest from 700- 1800 m where it actively forages in tangled vines and creepers in the forest undergrowth .
Gadopsis is a genus of temperate perches endemic to freshwater habitats in southeastern Australia .
Spartina bakeri is a species of grass known by the common names sand cordgrass and bunch cordgrass .
Tribolonotus ponceleti is a species of lizard in the Scincidae family .
Sayellini is a taxonomic tribe of minute ectoparasitic sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs , or micromollusks , in the very large family Pyramidellidae , the pyrams and their allies .
The Acidithiobacillales are an order of bacteria within the Class Acidithiobacillia and comprises the genera Acidithiobacillus and Thermithiobacillus .
Tetropium fuscum or the brown spruce longhorn beetle is a species of beetle in the Cerambycidae family .
Brachybembras aschemeieri is a species of deep - water flathead known only from the Pacific Ocean around the Philippines where it is found at a depth of around 582 metres ( 1,909 ft ) .
Amolops gerbillus is a species of frog found in Asia .
Xyris elliottii , Elliott 's yelloweyed grass , is a North American species of flowering plant in the yellow - eyed - grass family .
Archaephippus is an extinct genus of prehistoric spadefish that lived from the early to middle Eocene .
The Atelostomata are a superorder of sea urchins .
Carodnia is an extinct genus of South American ungulate known from the Paleocene of Brazil and Argentina , and the Eocene of Peru .
Vaccinium deliciosum is a species of bilberry known by the common names Cascade bilberry , Cascade blueberry , and blueleaf huckleberry .
Guillenia is a small genus of mustard plants containing three species .

Millerettidae is an extinct family of parareptiles from the Middle Permian to the Late Permian period ( Capitanian - Changhsingian stages ) of South Africa .

Prunus eremophila is a rare species of plum that is known by its common name Mojave Desert plum .

Luciobarbus kersin is a species of cyprinid fish found in freshwater habitats in Iran , Syria and southeastern Turkey .
The Australian rainbowfish ( Melanotaenia fluviatilis ) , known less commonly as the Murray River rainbowfish or the crimson - spotted rainbowfish , is a species of freshwater rainbowfish endemic to Australia .
Epidendrum magnoliae , sometimes called Epidendrum conopseum or the green - fly orchid , is a species of orchid in the genus Epidendrum .
Ctenochasma ( meaning ' comb jaw ' ) is a genus of Late Jurassic pterosaur belonging to the suborder Pterodactyloidea .
Trogloraptor is a genus of large spiders found in the caves of southwestern Oregon .
Enchelyurus flavipes is a species of combtooth blenny from the western Pacific Ocean .
Aristolochia scytophylla is a species of flowering plant in the family Aristolochiaceae .
The Drooping Shadowdamsel , ( Drepanosticta lankanensis ) is a species of damselfly in the family Platystictidae .
Pseudometapterus umbrosus is a species of assassin bug found in North America .
The Cape eagle - owl ( Bubo capensis ) is a species of owl in the family Strigidae .
Callundine lacordairei is a species of longhorn beetle in the Lamiinae subfamily , and the only species in the genus Callundine .
Nassarius candens , common name the bright nassa , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Nassariidae , the Nassa mud snails or dog whelks .
Nanorana ventripunctata ( common names : Yunnan slow frog , spot - bellied plateau frog ) is a species of frog in the Dicroglossidae family .
Wodnika is an extinct genus of shark which lived in the Late Permian period in the present area of Germany and Russia .
Restrepia , abbreviated Rstp in horticultural trade , is a small genus of 49 orchids in the orchid family ( Orchidaceae ) , closely related to Pleurothallis .
Osmitopsis is a genus of African flowering plants in the chamomile tribe within the daisy family .
Rubus geniculatus is a European species of flowering plant in the rose family , with a few naturalized populations in the State of Virginia in the eastern United States .
Prunum roscidum , common name the seaboard marginella , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Marginellidae , the margin snails .
Bidens bipinnata is a common and widespread species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
Solidago leavenworthii , Leavenworth 's goldenrod , is North American species of herbaceous perennial plants of the sunflower family .
Condylocardiidae is a family of small marine bivalve clams of the order Veneroida .
Galium californicum is a species of flowering plant in the coffee family known by the common name California bedstraw .
Stachytarpheta urticifolia , the nettleleaf velvetberry , is a species of flowering plant in the verbena family .
Callinectes arcuatus is a species of swimming crab in the genus Callinectes that lives along the Pacific coast of Central America .
Peperomia galioides is a species of plant in the Piperaceae family , endemic to Peru .
Synaptolaemus cingulatus is a species of headstander found in Brazil and Venezuela .
Viburnum tinus ( Laurustinus , laurustinus viburnum , or laurestine ) is a species of flowering plant in the family Adoxaceae , native to the Mediterranean area of Europe and North Africa .
Endopterygota , also known as Holometabola , is a superorder of insects of the subclass Pterygota which go through distinctive larval , pupal , and adult stages .
Megalictis ( great weasel ) is an extinct genus of large predatory mustelids , which existed in North America during the `` cat gap '' in the Miocene period .
Goneplacoidea is a superfamily of crabs containing 11 extant families , and two families known only from fossils ( marked `` † '' ) .
Sinomenium is a genus of plant in family Menispermaceae first described as a genus in 1910 .
Anomalochromis thomasi is a species of fish in the family Cichlidae , the only species in the genus Anomalochromis .
Oedipodiella is a genus of moss in the family Gigaspermaceae ; it contains the single species Oedipodiella australis .
Piabucina is a genus of freshwater fishes found in Central and South America .
Holospira mesolia , common name widemouth holospira , is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Urocoptidae .
Gobius senegambiensis is a species of goby native to the Atlantic Ocean from Morocco to Angola as well as the islands in the Gulf of Guinea where it is found in inshore waters on sandy substrates .
Pronothobranchius is a genus of African rivulines native to western Africa .
Bombus caliginosus , the obscure bumblebee , is a species of bumblebee native to the West Coast of the United States , where its distribution extends from Washington through Oregon to Southern California , as far south as the San Jacinto Mountains .
Ginsburgellus novemlineatus , the Nineline goby , is a species of goby native to tropical reefs of the western Atlantic Ocean and the Caribbean Sea .
Borealaspis is an extinct genus of Trilobite .
Acacia monticola , commonly known as red wattle or gawar , is a species of plant in the legume family that is native to northern Australia from Western Australia eastwards through the Northern Territory to central western Queensland .
Herina pseudoluctuosa is a species of picture - winged fly in the genus Herina of the family Ulidiidae found in Hungary , Italy , and Switzerland .
Oonops placidus is a spider species found in France .
Penstemon gracilentus is a species of penstemon known by the common names slender beardtongue and slender penstemon .
Cambaroides dauricus is a species of crayfish endemic to north - eastern China , the Korean Peninsula and neighbouring parts of Russia .
Aviculopecten is an extinct genus of bivalve mollusc that lived from the Early Devonian to the Late Triassic in Asia , Australia , Europe , North America , and South America .
Bucculatrix gossypina larvae feed on Gossypium species .
Sphaerosyllis levantina is a species belonging to the phylum Annelida , a group known as the segmented worms .
Prostanthera striatiflora , commonly known as Jockey 's Cap or Striped Mintbush , is a shrub species that occurs in the dry interior region of Australia .
Cantrainea sunderlandi is a species of small sea snail with calcareous opercula , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Colloniidae .
Macrotristria is a genus of cicada in the cryptotympanini tribe of the Cicadinae subfamily .
Athabascasaurus is an extinct genus of platypterygiine ophthalmosaurid ichthyosaur known from Alberta , Canada .
Moraea aristata ( Blue - eyed Uintjie or Blouooguintjie in Afrikaans ) is a critically endangered species of plant in the genus Moraea , that is endemic to the city of Cape Town and is now restricted to the grounds of the Observatory in the Cape Town suburb of Observatory .
Dorstenia erythranda is a species of herb in the plant family Moraceae which is native to Cuba and Hispaniola .
Columbarium veridicum is a species of deepwater sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Turbinellidae , the pagoda shells .
Gibbula multicolor , common name the multicoloured topshell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Naucoridae is a small family of insects commonly known as the creeping water bugs .
Pherosphaera fitzgeraldii , commonly known as the Blue Mountains Pine or Dwarf Mountain Pine is a species of conifer in the family Podocarpaceae .
Argiope savignyi is a species of orb - weaving spider that occurs from Mexico to Bolivia .
Cremohipparion is an extinct genus of horse living in Eurasia and Africa during the Miocene through Pliocene .
Cambrorhytium is an enigmatic fossil genus known from the Latham shale ( California ) , and the Chengjiang ( China ) and Burgess Shale ( Canadian rockies ) lagerstätte 350 specimens of Cambrorhytium are known from the Greater Phyllopod bed , where they comprise 0.7 % of the community .
Acreana cuprea is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Acreana .
Ancistroteuthis lichtensteinii , also known as the angel clubhook squid or simply angel squid , is a species of squid in the family Onychoteuthidae and the sole member of the genus Ancistroteuthis .
Scorpaenopsis is a genus of scorpionfishes native to the Indian and Pacific Oceans .
Rheocles vatosoa is a species of fish in the Bedotiidae family .
Eriogonum rosense is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name rosy buckwheat .
Santalum haleakalae , known as Haleakala sandalwood or ʻIliahi in Hawaiian , is a species of flowering tree in the European mistletoe family , Santalaceae , that is endemic to the island of Maui in the Hawaiian Islands , part of the United States .
Sminthurinus is a genus of collembola described by Börner in 1901 .
Coenobita violascens is a species of land hermit crab native to the Nicobar Islands , Thailand , Cambodia , Philippines , Japan and Tanzania .
Cormocephalus brachyceras is an Australian species of centipede from the genus Cormocephalus .
Galium litorale , Sicilian seashore bedstraw , is a rare species of plants in the Rubiaceae .
Rosa pimpinellifolia , the burnet rose , is a species of rose native to western , central and southern Europe ( north to Iceland and Norway ) and northwest Africa .
Licuala ferruginea is a species of palm tree from the genus Licuala .
Pseudomulciber salomonum is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudomulciber .
Phrynobatrachus latifrons ( common name : Ahl 's river frog ) is a species of frog in the Phrynobatrachidae family .
Agapanthus inapertus , ( Drakensberg Agapanthus or Drooping Agapanthus ) is a species of Agapanthus , native to open grasslands , forest margins and mountainous , rocky areas of Mozambique , Swaziland , and South Africa ( Transvaal and Natal ) .
Coptis laciniata is a species of flowering plant in the buttercup family known by the common name Oregon goldthread .
Potentilla arenaria is a plant species in the genus Potentilla .
Diacamma indicum , also known as Indian queenless ant , is a species of ant of the subfamily Ponerinae .
Sidalcea hartwegii is a species of flowering plant in the mallow family known by the common names valley checkerbloom and Hartweg 's checkerbloom .
Crataegus holmesiana is a species of hawthorn closely related to Scarlet Hawthorn , C. coccinea ( often incorrectly called C. pedicellata ) , but with more elongated fruit and leaves .
Psittacanthus robustus is a species of neotropical mistletoe in the Loranthaceae family that can be found growing on Vochysiaceae species in southeastern Brazil .
Tonlesapia is a genus of freshwater dragonets native to Southeast Asia .
Malus angustifolia , or southern crabapple , is a species of crabapple native to the eastern and south - central United States from Florida west to eastern Texas and north to New Jersey , Pennsylvania , Illinois and Missouri .
Cantharidus , common name the kelp shells , is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs of the family Trochidae , the top shells .
The genus contains only one species , i.e. Wittmackanthus stanleyanus , which is found in Panama , Colombia , Ecuador , Peru and Guyana .
Myrmoteras binghamii is a species of ant in the subfamily Formicinae .
Conus gladiator , common name the gladiator cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
It contains only one species , Pedaliotis dryograpta , which is found in Brazil .
Scartella poiti is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the southwest Atlantic ocean , around Trindade Island , Brazil .
Parapuzosia seppenradensis is the largest known species of ammonite .
Gnathodolus bidens is a species of headstander endemic to the Orinoco and Casiquiare rivers in Venezuela .
Pseudocreobotra is a genus of Sub - Saharan flower mantisses .
The Coachella Valley fringe - toed lizard ( Uma inornata ) is a species of phrynosomatid lizard .
Anoectochilus brevilabris is a species of orchid native to the mountains of Sikkim , Nepal , Assam , India , and Vietnam .
Malapterurus punctatus is a species of electric catfish native to Côte d'Ivoire , Guinea , Liberia and Sierra Leone .
Coelacanthopsis is an extinct genus of lobe - finned fish which lived during the Carboniferous period .
Michelia aenea is a species of plant in the Magnoliaceae family native to China and Vietnam .
Carex leporinella is a species of sedge known by the common name Sierra hare sedge .
Turbo sarmaticus , common name the South African turban , is a species of sea snail , marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinidae .
The Caponioidea or caponioids are a group of haplogyne araneomorph spiders that have been treated as superfamily with two members , the families Caponiidae and Tetrablemmidae .
Pelmatops is a genus of tephritid fruit flies .
Trachyphrynium is a monotypic genus of plants native to tropical Africa .
Viola nuttallii ( Nuttall 's violet , Yellow prairie violet ) is a perennial herbaceous plant in the Violet family ( Violaceae ) , and is one of the few violet species with lanceolate leaves .
The Ichthyostegidae is a small family of extinct labyrinthodont amphibian from the Devonian .
Mitracarpus maxwelliae is a rare species of flowering plant in the coffee family known by the common name Maxwell 's girdlepod .
The Ficedula flycatchers are a genus of Old World flycatchers .
The type species is Leedsichthys problematicus .
Itemirus is a genus of theropod dinosaur from the Turonian age of the Late Cretaceous period of Uzbekistan .
Pelecus cultratus , known variously as the sichel , the ziege , the sabre carp or sabrefish , is a species of cyprinid fish from an Eastern Europe and adjacent Asian regions .
Microcystis aeruginosa is a species of freshwater cyanobacteria which can form harmful algal blooms of economic and ecological importance .
Lutungutali ( meaning `` high hip '' in the Bemba language ) is an extinct genus of silesaurid dinosauriform from the Middle Triassic of Zambia .
Shorea maxima ( also called Yellow Meranti ) is a species of plant in the family Dipterocarpaceae .
Curvinomia formosa is a species of bees in the genus Curvinomia , of the family Halictidae .
Pseudarmadillo is a genus of woodlice from the Greater Antilles .

Menegazzia subpertusa is a species of lichen found in New Zealand , Australia , and South America .
It contains the single species Disasuridia rubida .
Ceanothus megacarpus is a species of flowering shrub known by the common name bigpod ceanothus .
Millerichthys robustus , the Mexican rivulus , is a species of rivuline endemic to Mexico where it is found in the Papaloapan and Coatzacoalcos River basins .
Bidens lemmonii ( Lemmon 's beggarticks ) is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
It is the only known species in the genus Hakonechloa .
Dichelostemma congestum is a species of flowering plant known by the common names roundtooth snakelily , manyflower brodiaea and wild hyacinth .
Imperator torosus , commonly known as the brawny bolete , is a species of bolete fungus in the family Boletaceae .
Pseudunela viatoris is a species of sea slug , an acochlidian , a shell - less marine gastropod mollusk in the family Pseudunelidae .
Toxicodendron succedaneum , the wax tree , Japanese wax tree or sơn in Vietnam , is a flowering plant species in the genus Toxicodendron found in Asia , although it has been planted elsewhere , most notably Australia and New Zealand .
The Enterobacteriaceae are a large family of Gram - negative bacteria that includes , along with many harmless symbionts , many of the more familiar pathogens , such as Salmonella , Escherichia coli , Yersinia pestis , Klebsiella and Shigella .
Alvaradoa amorphoides is a species of plant in the Picramniaceae family .
Eriogonum prattenianum is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name Nevada City buckwheat .

Eugeneodontida is an extinct and poorly known order of bizarre cartilaginous fishes .
Pocillopora grandis , is one of fifteen described species in the family Pocilloporidae .
The Eulophidae are a large family of hymenopteran insects , with over 4,300 described species in some 300 genera .
Carnegiella schereri , a species of hatchetfish , is native to the Amazon Basin in Peru and Brazil .

Cheilanthes distans is a species of lip fern known by the common name Bristly Cloak Fern .

Callochromis pleurospilus is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika excepting the southern end .
It was described by McCoy in 1849 , and the type species is Chasmops odini , which was originally described under the genus Calymene by Eichwald in 1840 .

Mariosousa usumacintensis is a plant species native to the Mexican State of Tabasco .
Pleurobrachia is a common genus of Ctenophora .

Eumetula bouvieri is a species of sea snail , a gastropod in the family Newtoniellidae , which is known from European waters .

Parexarrhenus excellens is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Parexarrhenus .
The Strelitziaceae comprise a family of monocotyledonous flowering plants , very similar in appearance and growth habit to members of the related families Heliconiaceae and Musaceae ( banana family ) .
Araeostoma aenicta is a moth in the Xyloryctidae family , and the only species in the genus Araeostoma .
Pittas are a family , Pittidae , of passerine birds mainly found in tropical Asia and Australasia , although a couple of species live in Africa .
Amsinckia lycopsoides is a species of fiddleneck known by the common name tarweed fiddleneck .
Nuculanidae is a family of small saltwater clams , marine bivalve molluscs in the order Nuculanoida .
Pisolithus arrhizus ( also spelled Pisolithus arhizus ) is a widespread earth - ball like fungus , which may in fact be several closely related species .
Allium zebdanense is a Middle Eastern species of wild onion found in Israel , Palestine , Syria , Lebanon , Turkey , Caucasus and Jordan .
Elymus farctus is a species of grass known by the common name sand couch - grass It is found in Europe and temperate Asia , and grows from rhizomes .
Cancellicula is a genus of medium - sized sea snails , marine gastropod molluscs in the family Cancellariidae , the nutmeg snails .
Tachina vernalis is a species of fly in the genus Tachina of the family Tachinidae that is endemic to US state of New Mexico .
Neochoerus pinckneyi was a North American species of capybara .
Ameles dumonti is a species of praying mantis that inhabits Tunisia and Morocco .
Ceratostylis is a genus of orchids with more than 140 species distributed in China , India , Southeast Asia , New Guinea , the Philippines , and Melanesia .
Perissoneura paradoxa is a species of picture - winged fly in the genus Perissoneura of the family Ulidiidae .
Spirodela punctata ( or Landoltia punctata , common name dotted duckmeat ) is a species of duckweed ( Lemnaceae ) .

Cadiouclanis is a genus of moths in the Sphingidae family , containing only one species , Cadiouclanis bianchii , which is known from Ethiopia .

Ecclinusa is a genus of plants in the Sapotaceae described as a genus in 1839 .

The Entomoplasmatales are a small order of mollicute bacteria .
