Hypolagus is an extinct genus of Lagomorpha , first recorded in the Hemingfordian ( early to middle Miocene ) of North America .
Habrodera nitidula is a small - bodied species , reaching about 9 - -11 millimetres ( 0.35 - -0.43 in ) in length .
Paracantha is a genus of tephritid fruit flies with ten described species .
Streptanthus bernardinus is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name Laguna Mountains jewelflower , or Laguna Mountain jewelflower .
Busycon is a genus of very large edible sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Busyconidae .
Alphamenes is a small neotropical genus of potter wasps currently containing 7 species .
Cytophaga is a genus of Gram - negative , gliding , rod - shaped bacteria .
Pococera cyrilla is a species of snout moth in the genus Pococera .
Tomaspis inclusa is a species of true bug from the Cercopidae family .
Gymnocondylus is a genus of Brazilian flowering plants in the daisy family , Asteraceae .
Caryoteae is a palm tree tribe in the family Arecaceae .
Isomoralla eriscota is a species of Oecophoridae that occurs in Australia .
Leucosporidium frigidum is a species of yeast that belongs to the genus of fungi Leucosporidium , and the family Leucosporidiaceae .
Trimma nasa , commonly called the nasal dwarfgoby or nasal pygmy goby , is a species of goby from the Western Pacific .
Mangelia costulata is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Mangeliidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Dermestidae are a family of Coleoptera that are commonly referred to as skin beetles .
Crassinella lunulata , or the lunate crassinella , is a species of very small bivalve mollusc in the family Crassatellidae .
Leavenworthia torulosa ( necklace gladecress ) is a species of plant in the mustard family .
Goeldia obscura is a spider species from Colombia and Peru .
Odostomia quadrae is a species of sea snail .
Hoita orbicularis is a species of legume known by the common name roundleaf leather - root .
The Chrysomeloidea are an enormous superfamily of beetles , with tens of thousands of species , mostly in the families Cerambycidae ( the long - horned beetles ) and Chrysomelidae , the leaf beetles .
Pistacia cucphuongensis is a species of plant in the Anacardiaceae family .
Paramurosternum pictum is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Paramurosternum .
The white sardinella , ( Sardinella albella ) , also known as Deep - bodied sardine , Perforated - scale sardine or Short - bodied sardine , is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Sardinella .
Bursina nobilis , common name the noble frog shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Bursidae , the frog shells .
Retimohnia caelata , common name : the plump whelk , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Buccinidae , the true whelks .
Sepia limata is a species of cuttlefish native to the southwestern Pacific Ocean , specifically southern Queensland to New South Wales , Australia ( 26 ° 30′S 153 ° 44′E to 34 ° 40′S 150 ° 51′E ) .
Spiraea nipponica is a species of flowering plant in the family Rosaceae , native to Japan .
Hymenoxys cooperi is a species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Cooper 's rubberweed .
Cirrhinus rubirostris is a species of cyprinid fish endemic to the Tenasserim River basin in southeastern Myanmar .
Anetia is a Neotropical genus of nymphalid butterfly in the Danainae subfamily .
Eulithidium bellum , common name the shouldered pheasant shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Phasianellidae .
Tylomelania perfecta is a species of freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Pachychilidae .
Licuala is a genus of palms commonly found in tropical rainforests of southern China , Southeast Asia , the Himalayas , New Guinea and the western Pacific Ocean islands .
Thouvenotiana ichneumona is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Thouvenotiana .
The Chinese stripe - necked turtle ( Ocadia sinensis ) or golden thread turtle , is a species of turtle in the Geoemydidae family .
Galesauridae is a family of Therapsid reptiles .
Physaria kingii is a species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name King bladderpod .
Gastrolobium is a genus of flowering plants in the family Fabaceae .
Froelichia juncea is a plant species native to the Galápagos Islands of Ecuador .
Metacarcinus is a genus of crabs formerly included in the genus Cancer .
Striatanaesthetis lineatipennis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Striatanaesthetis .
Triteleia dudleyi is a species of flowering plant known by the common name Dudley 's triteleia .
Epilobium leptophyllum is a species of flowering plant in the evening primrose family known by the common names bog willowherb and linear - leaved willowherb .
Hemicyclaspis ( meaning half - round shield or semicircle plate ) is an extinct genus of primitive jawless fish , closely related to Cephalaspis , that lived in the Devonian period in what is now Europe and North America .
Libys is a genus of the prehistoric coelacanth lobe - finned fish , an intermediary form between sea and land animals .
Silvetia is a genus of brown algae , commonly known as Rockweed , found in the intertidal zone of rocky seashores of the Pacific Ocean .
Astragalus shevockii is a rare species of milkvetch known by the common names Little Kern milkvetch and Shevock 's milkvetch .
Protea roupelliae is a species of protea in the large family of Proteaceae , and was named to commemorate Arabella Elizabeth Roupell ( 1817 - 1914 ) who spent two years in Cape Town and painted local flowers for her own pleasure .
Bonetto 's tuco - tuco ( Ctenomys bonettoi ) is a species of rodent in the family Ctenomyidae .
Arabibarbus arabicus is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Arabibarbus .
Cyathea fadenii is a species of tree fern endemic to the Uluguru Mountains in Tanzania , where it grows on exposed ridges and on the upper edge of montane forest at an altitude of 1700 - 2100 m. The trunk is erect , up to 4 m tall and 3 - 5 cm in diameter .
Mohnia parva is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Buccinidae , which is the true whelks .
Acer fabri ( Faber 's maple ) is a species of evergreen maple shrub native to Vietnam and central to southern China ( Guangdong , Guangxi , Guizhou , Hainan , Hubei , Hunan , Jiangxi , Sichuan , Yunnan ) .
Neosalangichthys ishikawae is a species of icefish endemic to Japan .
Axonopus fissifolius is a grass species which is often used as permanent pasture .
Echinelops is an extinct genus of elopiform ray - finned fish known from the Early Oligocene of Eastern Anatolia , Turkey .
Lepidogma rufescens is a species of snout moth in the genus Lepidogma .
Drymocallis is a genus of plants formerly ( and sometimes still ) included with the typical cinquefoils ( Potentilla ) .
Lactarius resimus is a species of mushrooms in the genus Lactarius , which is considered a delicacy in Russia and some other countries of Eastern Europe when pickled in salt .
Isoetes riparia ( shore quillwort ) is a species of quillwort in the Isoetaceae family .
Psophus stridulus , commonly known as the rattle grasshopper , is a species of grasshopper of the family Acrididae .
Koremaguia is a genus of moth in the Pterophoridae family containing only one species , Koremaguia alticola , which is found in India ( the Andaman Islands ) .
Galium rubrum is a plant species in the Rubiaceae .
Rosa stellata is a species of rose known by the common names desert rose , gooseberry rose , and star rose .
Actinella laciniosa is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Hygromiidae , the hariry snails and their allies .
The Yunnan hare ( Lepus comus ) is a species of mammal in the family Leporidae .
Castorocauda is a genus of small , semi - aquatic mammal relatives living in the Jurassic period , around 164 million years ago , found in lakebed sediments of the Daohugou Beds of Inner Mongolia .
Formotosena seebohmi is a cicada species from Taiwan , China , Vietnam and Japan .
Xylota is a genus of hoverflies similar in structure to the related genera Chalcosyrphus and Brachypalpoides .
Halichoeres richmondi , commonly called the Richmond 's wrasse or chain - lined wrasse , is a fish species in the wrasse family native from the central Indo - Pacific .
Eulophia is a genus of approximately 165 species of orchids .
The family Rhamphorhynchidae was named in 1870 by Harry Govier Seeley .
The Caryophylliidae are a family of stony corals found from the tropics to temperate seas , and from shallow to very deep water .
The pygmy falcons , Polihierax , are a genus of bird of prey in the Falconidae family .
Psilocybe subcaerulipes ( commonly known as Hikageshibiretake in Japanese ) is a species of fungus in the family Strophariaceae .
Carabus obsoletus nagyagensis is a subspecies of ground beetle in the Carabinae subfamily , that is endemic to Romania .
Penicillium tricolor is a species of the genus of Penicillium which was isolated from wheat in Canada .
Knema attenuata is a species of plant in the Myristicaceae family .
Donacia thalassina is a species of leaf beetle of the subfamily Donaciinae .
Mastax thermarum is a species of beetle in the Carabidae family that can be found in Asia and Europe .
Euglossa bazinga is a euglossine bee species found in Brazil .
The genus Sylvia is now restricted to Old World species of the family Sylviidae , unrelated to species such as the Nashville warbler , that are classified in the New World warbler family Parulidae .
Echaristha pictipennis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Echaristha .
The Evorsk vole ( Microtus evoronensis ) is a species of rodent in the family Cricetidae .
Psylloidea is a superfamily of true bugs , including the jumping plant lice and others which have recently been classified as distinct families .
Dracula wallisii is a species of orchid belonging to the genus Dracula .
Camissoniopsis bistorta is a species of flowering plant in the evening primrose family known by the common names southern suncup and California suncup .
Paramantis nyassana is a species of praying mantis in genus Paramantis .
The genus Buginbaatar was named by Kielan - Jaworowska Z. and Sochava A.V. in 1969 based on the remains of a single species .
Turtur is a small genus of doves native to Sub - Saharan Africa .
Achyranthes mutica ( also called blunt chaff flower ) is a species of plant in the Amaranthaceae family .
Rhadine persephone is a rare species of beetle known by the common name Tooth Cave ground beetle .
Aetoxylon is a single species genus ( monotypic ) of trees only found ( endemic ) in Borneo , of the flowering plant family Thymelaeaceae .
Goetzea elegans ( also called beautiful goetzea , mata buey , or matabuey ) is a species of plant in the Solanaceae or nightshade family of flowering plants .
Platymantis diesmosi is a species of frog that was first described by Brown and Gonzalez in 2007 .
Dyticonastis is an extinct genus of amphisbaenian or worm lizard that includes a single species , Dyticonastis rensbergeri , that lived during the late Oligocene and early Miocene in what is now Oregon .
Cyathea aneitensis is a species of tree fern native to Vanuatu and possibly New Caledonia .
Physaria tumulosa is a rare species of flowering plant in the mustard family known by the common name Kodachrome bladderpod .
The Benguet bush warbler ( Locustella seebohmi ) is a songbird species .
Denaeaspis is an extinct genus of tortoise beetle in the family Chrysomelidae and containing a single species Denaeaspis chelonopsis .
Propliopithecus is an extinct genus of primate .
Thermoanaerobacter italicusis a species of thermophilic , anaerobic , sporeformingbacteria .
Carinaria cristata , commonly known as the glassy nautilus , is a species of pelagic marine gastropod mollusc in the family Carinariidae .
Malacothamnus ( bush mallow ) is a genus of malvaceous plants native to California , and related to the Iliamnas of the US interior and the Phymosias of Mexico , Central America , and the Caribbean .
Placochelys ( ' flat - plate turtle `` ) is an extinct genus of placodont reptiles .
Flabellipecten flabelliformis is an extinct species of large scallops or saltwater clams , marine bivalve mollusks in the family Pectinidae , the scallops .
Calochortus weedii is a North American species of flowering plants in the lily family known by the common name Weed 's mariposa lily .
It contains only one known species , Aganonerion polymorphum , native to Indochina ( Thailand , Laos , Cambodia , Vietnam ) .
Frasera speciosa is a species of flowering plant in the Gentian Family ( Gentianaceae ) known by the common names elkweed , deer 's ears , and monument plant .
Alphasphaerolipovirus is a proposed genus of double stranded DNA viruses that infect haloarchaea .
Tarchonanthus is a genus of flowering plants in the mutisia tribe daisy family .
Conus archon , common name the magistrate cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Diploconger polystigmatus , or the headband conger , is a species of eel in the family Congridae .
Bacillus atticus atticus is a species of phasmid or `` walking stick '' with recorded specimens in Greece , Italy , Croatia and Israel .
Megistotherium ( from Greek , megistos `` greatest '' + therion `` beast '' and osteon ' bone ' + thlaston ' crushed , bruised ' with -es being an agent noun : ' bone - crusher ' ) is an extinct genus of hyaenodontid , the only known species of which is Megistotherium osteothlastes .
Diasybra ochreobasalis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Diasybra .
Oxyaena ( `` Sharp '' or `` Drawn - out '' + hyena ) is an extinct genus of oxyaenid mammal from the latest Paleocene to early Eocene of North America ( most specimens being found in Colorado ) .
Conus anningae is an extinct species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails , cone shells or cones .
Hemarthria is a genus of herbaceous plants in the grass family .
Columbinia elegans is a left - handed , air - breathing land snail species in the genus Columbinia .
Gryllomorpha dalmatina is a species of cricket belonging to the family Gryllidae subfamily Gryllomorphinae .
The Usambara akalat ( Sheppardia montana ) , also known as the Usambara alethe or Usambara robin - chat , is a species of bird in the family Muscicapidae .
Theskelomensor creon is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Endodontidae .
Orectochilus orbisonorum is a species of whirligig beetle named in honor of Roy and Barbara Orbison .
Lilium kelleyanum is a California species of lily known by the common name Kelley 's lily .
The genus is monotypic , containing the single species Paurocotylis pila , a truffle - like fungus found in Europe and New Zealand .
Oxygaster is a genus of cyprinid fishes found in Southeast Asia .
Anelosimus guacamayos is a species of social cobweb spider that occurs in the lower Ecuadorian sierra .
Atherinosoma is a genus of silversides .
Diplopora is a genus of marine dasycladacean algae in the family Diploporaceae .
The Puerto Rican tanager eats palm fruits , ants and species from the Cecropia genus .
Rhabdoblennius rhabdotrachelus , the Barchin blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in the Pacific ocean .
Turbinella pyrum , common names the chank shell , sacred chank or chank , also known as the divine conch , sometimes referred to simply as a conch , is a species of very large sea snail with a gill and an operculum , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Turbinellidae .
Selenosteidae is a family of small to large - sized arthrodire placoderms from the Late Devonian .
Cnidospora is a defunct subphylum of microscopic spore - forming parasites in the defunct phylum Protozoa .
Desmoscolecida is an order of marine nematodes .
Xysmalobium is a genus of the botanical family Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1810 .
Jasminum humile , the Italian jasmine or yellow jasmine , is a species of flowering plant in the Oleaceae family , native to Afghanistan , Tajikistan , Pakistan , Nepal , Burma ( Myanmar ) , the Himalayas and south west China ( Gansu , Guizhou , Sichuan , Xizang ( Tibet ) , Yunnan ) .
Pyrgacris descampsi is a species of insect , belonging to the family of Pyrgacrididae .
Orsonwelles torosus is a species of linyphiid spider endemic to Kauai in the Hawaiian Islands .
Tanea zelandica , common name the necklace shell or the New Zealand Moon Snail , is a species of medium - sized sea snail , a predatory marine gastropod mollusc in the Family Naticidae , the moon snails or necklace shells .
Echinops ritro ( southern globethistle ) is a species of flowering plant in the sunflower family , native to southern and eastern Europe ( from Spain east to Turkey , Ukraine , and Belarus ) , and western Asia .
Setaria barbata , with common names bristly foxtail grass , corn grass , Mary grass , and East Indian bristlegrass , is a species of grass in the Poaceae family native to tropical Africa and tropical Asia .
Tacca chantrieri , the black bat flower , is a species of flowering plant in the yam family Dioscoreaceae .
Dysderina is a genus of goblin spider
Brickellia rusbyi ( stinking brickellbush ) is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Pycnanthus angolensis is a species of tree in the nutmeg family , Myristicaceae .
Consolea is a genus of cacti , named after Italian botanist Michelangelo Console .
Tuleariocaris neglecta is a species of saltwater shrimp found in the Maldives that was first described in 1969 .
Lufengpithecus keiyuanensis is a prehistoric species of orangutan from the Late Miocene to the Pliocene of China .
Rosopsida ( Batsch , 1788 ) is a botanical name for a group of flowering plants recognized at the rank of class .
Exelastis dowi is a species of moth in the genus Exelastis , known from the Bahamas , Belize and Florida .
Conus balteatus , common name the Mauritian cone , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae , the cone snails and their allies .
Leptopoecile is a genus of bird in the long - tailed tit family Aegithalidae .
The type and only species , Cherminotus longifrons , was named in 1984 .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Lindauella pyrenocarpoidea .
Drupa clathrata , common name : the clathrate drupe , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Muricidae , the murex snails or rock snails .
Copaxa lavendera is a species of moth in the family Saturniidae .
The Santa Lucia Mountains slender salamander ( Batrachoseps luciae ) is a species of salamander in the Plethodontidae family .
Arcantiodelphys is an extinct genus of basal Metatheria which existed in France during the Cenomanian age .
Widdringtonia nodiflora ( mountain cypress ) is a species of Widdringtonia native to Southern Africa .
Gonodactylaceus , is a genus of mantis shrimp .
Streptomyces humiferus is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil near Moscow in Russia .
Entamoebidae is a family of Archamoebae .
Species There is only one accepted species , Schizoptera peduncularis , native to Peru and Ecuador .
It contains a single species , the Prickly Skink , ( Gnypetoscincus queenslandiae ) .
Gymnadenia rhellicani is a European species of orchid .
Parachromis dovii , the Guapote , is a species of cichlid native to Central America where it occurs on both slopes of Honduras , Nicaragua and Costa Rica .
Palaeobalistum goedeli is an extinct species of prehistoric bony fish lived during the Cretaceous period .
Coryphaenoides leptolepis , the Ghostly grenadier , is a species of rattail found in the northern Atlantic and Pacific Oceans at depths of 610 to 4,000 metres ( 2,000 to 13,120 ft ) .
Exocarpos sparteus is an Australian endemic plant species , commonly known as the broom ballart , slender cherry , or native cherry .
Sandalops melancholicus , the sandal - eyed squid , is a species of glass squid .
Pedinoida is an order of sea urchins , containing the single living genus Caenopedina .
Urocordylinae is an extinct subfamily of lepospondyl amphibians that includes several small newt - like species with short skulls and elongated , flattened tails .
Pritchardiopsis jeanneneyi is a species of flowering plant in the Arecaceae family , and the only species in the genus Pritchardiopsis .
Leptomys arfakensis is a species of rodent in the family of Muridae
Placodermi ( from the Greek πλάξ = plate and δέρμα = skin , literally `` plate - skinned '' ) is an extinct class of armoured prehistoric fish , known from fossils , which lived from the Silurian to the end of the Devonian Period .
Priolepis cincta , commonly known as the Girdled goby is a species of goby fish described by Regan in 1908 .
Butis is a genus of sleeper gobies found in fresh , brackish , and marine waters from the Indian Ocean coast of Africa through Southeast Asia to the Pacific islands and Australia .
Sasaella is a genus of Japanese bamboo in the grass family .
Verbena californica is a rare species of verbena known by the common names California vervain and Red Hills vervain .
Ehrlichia canis is an obligate , intracellular bacterium that acts as the causative agent of Ehrlichiosis , a disease most commonly affecting canine species .
Elaeis guineensis is a species of palm commonly called African oil palm or macaw - fat .
Discothyrea antarctica is a species of ant in the genus Discothyrea , endemic to New Zealand .
Lupinus tidestromii , Tidestrom 's lupine , is a rare species of lupine known by the common names clover lupine and Tidestrøm 's lupine .
Malapterurus tanganyikaensis is a species of electric catfish native to Lake Tanganyika where it occurs in the bordering nations of Burundi , the Democratic Republic of the Congo , Tanzania and Zambia .
Hypsolebias magnificus is a species of rivuline fish native the Middle São Francisco River basin in Brazil .
Strombocactus disciformis is a rare species of cacti and the only species of the genus Strombocactus .
Pseudomoraria triglavensis is a species of copepod in the family Canthocamptidae .
Drynaria roosii , commonly known as Gu - Sui - Bu , is a species of basket fern of the family Polypodiaceae .
Musca vetustissima , commonly known as the Australian bush fly , is a species of fly found in Australia .
Physeteroidea is a superfamily that , today , includes three extant species of whales ; the sperm whale , in the genus Physeter , and the pygmy sperm whale and dwarf sperm whale , in the genus Kogia .
Pereskiopsis ( from Greek -opsis , `` looking '' , because of its resemblance with the genus Pereskia ) is a genus of cacti ( family Cactaceae ) .
Sorindeia is a genus of some three dozen plant species that are native to tropical Africa , Madagascar , the Comoro Islands and Mascarene Islands .
Dodonaea petiolaris is a shrub species in the genus Dodonaea found in Australia .
Craugastor augusti is a species of frog in the Craugastoridae family found in Mexico and the southern United States .
Gabrielona is a genus of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Phasianellidae .
Amphiodon effusus is a species of legume in the subfamily Faboideae .
It contains only one species , Setiarcha aleuropis , which is found in Brazil .
Porangonycha princeps is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Porangonycha .
Eucephalus paucicapitatus is a North American species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name Olympic Mountain aster .
Holcostethus albipes is a species of shield bugs belonging to the family Pentatomidae , subfamily Pentatominae .
Avicularia affinis is a species of spider belonging to the family Theraphosidae ( tarantulas ) .
Aenictus is a large army ant genus distributed in the Old World tropics and subtropics .
A single species , Zhangheotherium quinquecuspidens , is known .
Capelatus prykei is a species of diving beetle found on tha Cape Peninsula , close to Cape town South Africa .
Dendropsophus nanus ( common name : dwarf treefrog ) is a species of frog in the Hylidae family .
Trichoserixia rondoni is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Trichoserixia .
Allagopappus is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family described as a genus in 1828 .
Arctostaphylos rubra is a species of flowering plant in the heath family and the genus Arctostaphylos , the manzanitas and bearberries .
Cheilomenes is an Old World genus of ladybirds in the family Coccinellidae .
Crocidopoma is a genus of land snails with an operculum , terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the family Neocyclotidae .
Agrilus hyperici is a species of jewel beetle known by the common name St. John 's wort root borer .
Nicrophorus interruptus is a species of burying beetles or sexton beetles belonging to the family Silphidae subfamily Nicrophorinae .
Erosaria ocellata , common name the ocellate cowry , is a species of sea snail , a cowry , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cypraeidae , the cowries .
Braya thorild - wulffii , the Greenland northern rockcress , is a plant species native to Greenland , Nunavut the Canadian Northwest Territories , and from the Chukotka Autonomous Okrug of eastern Russia .
Sedum ochroleucum , the European stonecrop , is a species of Sedum , native to Europe and Turkey .
Parobereopsis nigrosternalis is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Parobereopsis .
Catascopia terebra ( Westerlund , 1885 ) ( formerly known as Catascopia occulta ) is a species of air - breathing freshwater snail , an aquatic pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Lymnaeidae , the pond snails .
Tachina actinosa is a species of fly in the genus Tachina of the family Tachinidae that is endemic to the US state of Oregon .
It is thought that black rats inadvertently introduced by the expedition infected the Maclear 's rats with a disease ( possibly a trypanosome ) , which in turn may have contributed to the species decline .
Rivularia is a genus of cyanobacteria of the familia Rivulariaceae .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Poculopsis ogrensis .
Euparkeria ( /juːˌpɑrkəˈriːə/ ; meaning `` Parker 's good animal '' , named in honor of W.K. Parker ) is an extinct genus of archosauriform from the Middle Triassic of South Africa .
Pachliopta oreon is a species of butterfly from the family Papilionidae .
Lewisia is a plant genus , named for Meriwether Lewis who encountered the species in 1806 .
Caecum pulchellum , common name the beautiful caecum , is a species of minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Caecidae .
Trichoprosoplus demarzi is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Trichoprosoplus .
Corchorus walcottii , commonly known as woolly corchorus , is a shrub species in the family Malvaceae .
Papilio hoppo is a species of swallowtail butterfly from the genus Papilio that is found only in Taiwan .
The Formosan sika deer , ( Chinese : 台灣梅花鹿 ; pinyin : Táiwān méihuālù ; Pe̍h - ōe - jī : Tâi - oân hoe - lo̍k ) , is a subspecies of sika deer endemic to the island of Taiwan .
The False Puffball , Enteridium lycoperdon , is one of the more obvious species of slime mould or Myxogastria , typically seen in its reproductive phase as a white ' swelling ' on standing dead trees in the spring , or on large pieces of fallen wood .
Andreaea depressinervis is a species of moss that lives in South America and Antarctica .
Micropterix schaefferi is a species of moth belonging to the family Micropterigidae that was described by Heath in 1975 .
Lobelia tupa ( Tupa , Tabaco del diablo ) is a species of Lobelia native to central Chile from Valparaíso south to Los Lagos regions .
Oonops procerus is a spider species found in France and Spain .
Breviparopus ( ichnotype B. taghbaloutensis ) is the name given to an ichnogenus of dinosaur , having been made by an unknown genus of sauropod .
The green carab beetle or saffron beetle ( Calosoma schayeri ) is a species of Carabidae that occurs in Australia .
Mayna pubescens is a species of flowering plant in the Achariaceae family that is endemic to Colombia .
Greslania is a genus of shrubby bamboo in the grass family , endemic to New Caledonia .
Stanhopeinae is a subtribe of plants in the orchid family .
Thaumatoneura inopinata is a highly distinctive species , making up a monotypic genus ( Thaumatoneura ) and subfamily ( Thaumatoneurinae ) .
Kanuites is an extinct genus of viverrid native to Africa .
Sphodromantis tenuidentata , common name Tanzanian mantis , is a species of praying mantis found in Tanzania .
Comarostaphylis arbutoides is a species of shrub in the heath family .
Serranochromis janus is a species of cichlid endemic to the Malagarazi River in Tanzania preferring areas with plentiful vegetation and slow currents .
Their scientific name , Diporiphora winneckei , suggests they have two visible pores , however the pores are not visible on this species .
Lethrinops christyi is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Malawi where it is only known from the southern part of the lake .
The Cichlasomatinae are a subfamily of cichlid fishes , including all ciclids native to islands in the Caribbean ( Cuba and Hispaniola ) , USA ( southern Texas ) , Mexico and Central America , and many of the cichlids from South America ( the other South American subfamilies are Astronotinae , Cichlinae , Geophaginae , and Retroculinae ) .
Clappia is a genus of small freshwater snails that have an operculum , aquatic gastropod mollusks in the family Lithoglyphidae .
Mutinus ravenelii is a species of fungus that is often confused with M. elegans and M. caninus .
Xanthoria elegans , commonly known as the elegant sunburst lichen , is a lichenized species of fungus in the genus Xanthoria , family Teloschistaceae .
Crinum asiaticum ( poison bulb , giant crinum lily , grand crinum lily , spider lily ) is a plant species widely planted in many warmer regions as an ornamental .
Corbicula is a genus of freshwater and brackish water clams , aquatic bivalve mollusks in the family Cyrenidae , the basket clams .
Pimenta racemosa is a species of plant in the myrtle family ( Myrtaceae ) that is native to the Caribbean region .
Eriocaulon parkeri is a species of flowering plant in the pipewort family known by the common names Parker 's pipewort and estuary pipewort .
Rhus kearneyi is a species of flowering plant in the cashew family known by the common name Kearney 's sumac .
Abludomelita is a genus of amphipod crustacean .
The Leptanthuridae are a family of isopod crustaceans , containing the following genera :
Erigeron garrettii is a rare North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family known by the common name Garrett 's fleabane .
Heteronychus arator ( hetero+onychus = ' variable claw ' , arator = ' ploughman ' ) is a species of beetle in the subfamily Dynastinae ( the rhinoceros beetles ) .
Serinus is a genus of small birds in the finch family Fringillidae found in Europe and Africa .
Pestalotiopsis microspora is a species of endophytic fungus capable of breaking down and digesting polyurethane .
Parkia balslevii is a species of flowering plant in the pea family , Fabaceae , that is endemic to Ecuador .
Eunidiopsis bicolor is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Eunidiopsis .
Bean calico mosaic virus ( BCaMV or BCMoV ) is a plant virus transmitted by whiteflies that infects bean genera and species within the families Fabaceae , Malvaceae , and Solanaceae .
Tropidoptera heliciformis is a species of small , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Amastridae .
Pseudevernia furfuracea , commonly known as tree moss , is a lichenized species of fungus that grows on the bark of firs and pines .
Acacia tumida , known colloquially as pindan wattle , is a species of Acacia native to northern and western Australia .
Chilorhinophis carpenteri , or the Liwale two - headed snake , is a species of venomous snake in the Atractaspididae family .
Enneapterygius cheni is a species of threefin blenny in the genus Enneapterygius .
Porites nodifera , also known as Dome Coral , is a species of stony coral in the Poritidae family .
Acromantis hesione , common name Burmese mantis , is a species of praying mantis found in China and the Philippines .
The Maleae ( incorrectly Pyreae ) are the apple tribe in the rose family , Rosaceae .
Rhacophorus tunkui is a disputed species of frog in the moss frog family ( Rhacophoridae ) .
Protonaegleria is an amoeboid genus .
The Vesperidae are a small family of beetles , normally classified within the family Cerambycidae , of heterogeneous aspect but all characterised by larval stages related to roots of herbaceous plants or trees
Dryolestida is an extinct order of mammals ; most of the members are mostly known from the Jurassic to Paleogene , with one member , Necrolestes , surviving as late as early Miocene .
Austrostipa flavescens , commonly known as Coast Spear - grass , is a species of plant in the true grass family .
Stylospania is a genus of snipe fly of the family Rhagionidae .
The Pink Fairy Orchid ( Caladenia latifolia ) is species of orchid found across southern Australia .
Perplexicervix is a genus of bird appearing in the eleventh Mammal - Paleogene zone of Hessen , Germany .
Nama californicum is a species of flowering plant in the borage family known by the common name California fiddleleaf .
Acracona is a genus of snout moths in the subfamily Galleriinae .
Neosalanx tangkahkeii , the Chinese icefish , is a species of icefish endemic to China .
Malus fusca , with the common names Oregon crabapple and Pacific crabapple , is a North American species of crabapple .
Pecten albicans , common name Japanese baking scallop , is a species of marine bivalve mollusks in the family Pectinidae , the scallops .
Macropygia is a genus of bird in the pigeon and dove family Columbidae .
Mesogyrus is an extinct genus of fossil beetles in the family Gyrinidae , containing the following species :
Hymenoxys vaseyi is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family known by the common name Vasey 's rubberweed .
Tenodera fasciata is a species of mantis in the subfamily Mantinae of the family Mantidae .
Fritillaria purdyi , known by the common name Purdy 's fritillary , is a rare species of flowering plant in the lily family .
Lecanites is a ceratitid genus assigned to the Danubitaceae , with an essentially smooth , evolote , discoidal shell and a goniatitic suture with many elements .
Epedanidae is a family of the harvestman infraorder Grassatores with about 200 described species .
Nassarius globosus , common name the globose nassa , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Nassariidae , the Nassa mud snails or dog whelks .
The Chilean tree iguana , Liolaemus chiliensis , is a species of lizard in the Iguanidae family .
Psammogobius is a genus of gobies native to the Atlantic coast of South Africa through the Indian Ocean to the western Pacific Ocean .
Allocnemis leucosticta , the goldtail , is a species of damselfly in the family Platycnemididae .
Austroclupea is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish that lived during the Pliocene epoch .
Rhinella poeppigii ( commmon name : gray toad ) is a species of toad in the family Bufonidae that is known from the eastern Andean slopes of Ecuador , Peru , and Bolivia , as well as from Serranía de Sira in Amazonian Peru .
Jordanoleiopus bifuscoplagiatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the long - horned beetle .
Haemophilus paraphrophilus is a species of Haemophilus .
Missulena insignis , commonly known as the lesser red - headed mouse spider , is a species of spider belonging to the family Actinopodidae native to Australia .
Parsonsia is a genus of woody vines of the dogbane family , Apocynaceae .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Sivanesaniella prunicola .
Ingerana tenasserimensis ( common names : Tenasserim eastern frog , pale - headed frog ) is a species of frog in the Dicroglossidae family .
Spondias purpurea is a species in flowering plant in the cashew family , Anacardiaceae , that is native to tropical regions of the Americas .
Schistura reidi is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Schistura .
The Stenophlebiidae is an extinct family of medium - sized to large fossil odonates from the Upper Jurassic and Lower Cretaceous period that belongs to the damsel - dragonfly grade ( `` anisozygopteres '' ) within the stem group of Anisoptera .
Tillandsia cyanea ( common name pink quill ) is a species of flowering plant in the bromeliad family , native to the rainforests of Ecuador .
Exoglossum laurae ( common name tonguetied minnow ) is a species of minnow found in North America .
Diadema paucispinum , the long - spined sea urchin , is a species of sea urchin in the family Diadematidae .
Labroides bicolor is a species of wrasse endemic to the Indo - Pacific , Indian Ocean and Pacific Ocean and is known by various names including bicolor cleanerfish , bicolor cleaner wrasse , bicolored cleaner wrasse , bicolour cleaner wrasse , cleaner wrasse , two - colour cleaner wrasse and yellow diesel wrasse .
Asclepias cordifolia is a species of milkweed commonly called heart - leaf milkweed or purple milkweed ( a common name shared with another milkweed , Asclepias purpurascens ) .
Tropidodiscidae is an extinct family of Paleozoic fossil molluscs with isostrophically coiled shells .
Meliphagoidea is a superfamily of passerine birds .
Fistulina is a genus of fungi in the Fistulinaceae family .
Thelazia is a genus of nematode worms which parasitize the eyes and associated tissues of various bird and mammal hosts , including humans .
Barylambdidae is an extinct family of pantodont mammals from North America .
The mourning gecko or common smooth - scaled gecko ( Lepidodactylus lugubris ) is a species of gecko .
Passiflora caerulea , the blue passionflower , bluecrown passionflower or common passion flower , is a species of flowering plant native to South America ( Argentina , Chile , Paraguay , Uruguay and Brazil ) .
Polygonum pensylvanicum ( syn . Persicaria pensylvanica ) is a species of flowering plant in the buckwheat family , Polygonaceae .
Sceptrophasma hispidulum , commonly known as the Andaman Islands stick insect , is a species of the stick insect family .
Phenacosaurus vanzolinii is a species of lizards in the anolefamily .
Monoplex tranquebaricus , common name : the West African Hairy Triton , is a species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Ranellidae , the triton snails , triton shells or tritons .
Dysaules himalayanus is a species of praying mantis in the genus Dysaules .
Thelypteris pilosa is a species of fern known by the common names hairy maiden fern , softhairy maiden fern , and streak - sorus fern .
Salix pentandra ( bay willow ) is a species of willow native to northern Europe and northern Asia .
Calochortus persistens is a rare North American species of flowering plant in the lily family known by the common name Siskiyou mariposa lily .
Kageneckia oblonga ( also known as Bollen ) is a species of plant in the Rosaceae family .
Strigosuchus is an extinct genus of crurotarsan from the Early Jurassic of China .
Leonaspis is a widespread genus of odontopleurid trilobite that lived from the Late Ordovician to the early Devonian .
The Gabela akalat ( Sheppardia gabela ) is a species of bird in the family Muscicapidae .
Tylenchorhynchus is a genus of nematodes including many species of plant parasites .
Carabus dietererberi is a species of beetle from Carabidae family that is endemic to Sichuan , China .
Aristida behriana is a native Australian species of grass commonly known as bunch wire grass or brush wire grass .
Phiditiidae is a family of moths .
Dalbergia oliveri is a species of legume in the Fabaceae family which grows in tree form to 15 - 30 meters in height ( up to 100 ft . ) .
In taxonomy , Actinastrum is a genus of green algae , specifically of the class Chlorophyceae .
Heteroclinus flavescens , the Short - tassel weedfish , is a species of clinid native to the Pacific Ocean waters around New Zealand and Australia .
One of many species of manzanita , Arctostaphylos manzanita has the common names Common manzanita and Whiteleaf manzanita .
Eucalyptus pauciflora , commonly known as Snow Gum or White Sallee , is a species of flowering plant in the family Myrtaceae .
Sparganiaceae is the botanical name for a family of flowering plants .
Troilus luridus is a species of shield bug .
Acropora rambleri is a species of acroporid coral found in the Red Sea , the Gulf of Aden , the southwest and northern Indian Ocean , the central Indo - Pacific , Southeast Asia , Japan , the East China Sea , eastern Australia and the oceanic west and central Pacific Ocean .
Utricularia dichotoma , commonly known as fairy aprons , is a variable , perennial species of terrestrial bladderwort .
Ribes californicum , with the common name hillside gooseberry , is a North American species of currant .
Stagetus profundus is a species of beetles in the genus Stagetus of the family Anobiidae .
It contains only one species , Klimeschiola philetella , which is found in mainland Greece and on Crete .
Lavandula ( common name lavender ) is a genus of 39 known species of flowering plants in the mint family , Lamiaceae .
Bradysia similigibbosa is a species of fungus gnat from New Caledonia .
Pissarrachampsinae is a subfamily of baurusuchid crocodyliforms from the Late Cretaceous of Brazil and Argentina .
Viola tomentosa is a species of violet known by the common names feltleaf violet and woolly violet .
Achatina achatina , common name the giant Ghana snail , also known as the giant tiger land snail , is a species of very large , air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Achatinidae .
The Lybiidae is a bird family containing the African barbets .
Pachystropheus ( After Greek Pachys , `` Thick '' and Strophaios , Vertebrae ) is a genus of prehistoric reptile , possibly a choristodere ( champsosaur ) , from the Rhaetian ( Late Triassic ) of southwestern England .
Cryptoblastus is a genus of extinct blastoids , a primitive group of echinoderms related to the modern sea lilies .
Anguilla bicolor is a species of eel in the genus Anguilla of the family Anguillidae , consisting of two subspecies .
Emeraldella is a genus of artiopod arthropod known from the Middle Cambrian Burgess Shale .
Nipponites ( `` stone of Nippon '' ) is an extinct genus of heteromorph ammonites .
Anticarsia irrorata is a species of moth in the family Noctuidae known commonly as the owl moth .
Elasmias jaurffreti is a species of tropical tree - living air - breathing land snail , arboreal pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Achatinellidae .
Heteropneustes microps is a species of airsac catfish possibly endemic to Sri Lanka , though records from India have been made .
Anurognathus is a genus of small pterosaur that lived during the late Jurassic Period ( Tithonian stage ) .
Stark 's lark ( Spizocorys starki ) is a species of lark in the Alaudidae family .
Gongylophis colubrinus , the Kenyan sand boa , is a boa species found in northern Africa .
Lupinoblennius is a genus of combtooth blennies found in the western Atlantic Ocean .
Flabellina is a genus of sea slugs , specifically aeolid nudibranchs .
Myanmymar is an extinct genus of fairyfly preserved in amber from Myanmar .
Gagea bulbifera is an Eurasian species of plants in the lily family , widespread from Romania to Xinjiang .
Azteca andreae is an arboreal ant species found in the tropics of South America , most notably in French Guiana .
Edwardsina tasmaniensis or the Tasmanian torrent midge is a species of fly in family Blephariceridae .
Tachygerrini is a tribe of water striders .
Algansea amecae is a recently described species of freshwater fish in the family Cyprinidae .
Brachyuranochampsa is an extinct genus of crocodyloid crocodilians .
Malacothrix sonchoides is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common names sowthistle desertdandelion and yellow saucers .
Fenimorea is a genus of carnivorous sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Drilliidae .
Ameles persa is a species of praying mantis found in Afghanistan and Iran .
Musteloidea is a superfamily of carnivoran mammals united by shared characters of the skull and teeth .
Deinodryinus velteni is an extinct species of Deinodryinus in the wasp family Dryinidae .
Tuberculobasis macuxi is a species of damselfly in the family Coenagrionidae first identified in Roraima , Brazil .
Tomopterna damarensis is a species of frog in the Pyxicephalidae family endemic to Namibia .
The genus Henkelodon ( `` Henkel 's tooth '' ) was named by Hahn G. in 1977 based on a single species .
Phoebe zhennan is a large species of tree up to 30 metres ( 98 ft ) tall in the Lauraceae family .
It contains only one known species , Pachystylidium hirsutum , found in eastern India , Indochina , the Philippines , Sulawesi , the Lesser Sunda Islands , and Java .
Sarcocystis is a genus of protozoa .
Nidaliidae is a family of soft corals in the phylum Cnidaria .
Sertifera is a genus of flowering plants from the orchid family , Orchidaceae , native to northwestern South America .
Restrepia contorta , the Twisted Restrepia , is a species of orchid endemic to western South America .
Cucujinus coquereli is a beetle species in the family Laemophloeidae found on Reunion Island off the coast of Madagascar .
Macroptilium supinum is a species of flowering plant in the legume family known by the common name supine bean .
Harpegnathos is a small ponerine genus of ants found in South and Southeast Asia .
Kickxia elatine is a species of flowering plant in the Scrophulariaceae known by several common names , including sharpleaf cancerwort , sharppoint fluvellin and sharp - leaved fluvellin .
Saccharina is a genus of 20 species of Phaeophyceae ( brown algae ) .
Maackia amurensis , commonly known as the Amur maackia , is a species of tree in the Fabaceae family that can grow 15 metres ( 49 ft ) tall .
Romeosaurus is an extinct genus of yaguarasaurine mosasaur known from the early Late Cretaceous `` Lastame '' lithotype ( lower Turonian to lower Santonian ) of northern Italy .
The Parvoviridae are a family of small , rugged , genetically - compact DNA viruses , known collectively as parvoviruses .
Crotalus horridus , commonly known as the timber rattlesnake , canebrake rattlesnake or banded rattlesnake , is a species of venomous pit viper endemic to the eastern United States .
It consists of only one species , Ameleta panochra , which was described by Turner in 1940 .
Murdochella levifoliata is a species of minute wentletrap , a sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Nystiellidae , commonly known as wentletraps .
Parasphallenum fulguratum is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , the only species in the genus Parasphallenum .
Hymenaea verrucosa ( Zanzibar copal , East African copal , or Amber tree ) is a species of flowering plant in the legume family , Fabaceae .
Dasysyrphus tricinctus is a european species of hoverfly in the genus Dasysyrphus , a member of the family Syrphidae .
Aztlanolagus is an extinct monotypic genus of rabbit with a single species Aztlanolagus agilis .
Chaetonotidae is a family of gastrotrichs in the order Chaetonotida .
Candida antarctica is a yeast species in the genus Candida .
Striginiana is a genus of moth in the family Eupterotidae from Africa .
Aepus is a genus of ground beetles of the subfamily Trechinae .
The Ethiopian snout - burrower , Lake Zwai snout - burrower , or Lake Zwai shovelnose frog ( Hemisus microscaphus ) is a species of frog in the Hemisotidae family , endemic to Ethiopia .
Oligobunis is an extinct genus of mustelids , which existed during the Miocene epoch .
Idiacanthus is a genus of barbeled dragonfishes , the larvae of which are noted for exhibiting the Stylophthalmine trait .
Berosus quadridens is a species of hydrophilid beetle from Mexico , Guatemala , Nicaragua , Costa Rica and Cuba .
Polytrichum juniperinum , commonly known as juniper haircap or juniper polytrichum moss , is an evergreen and perennial species of moss that is widely distributed , growing on every continent including Antarctica .
Platystomos wallacei is a species of beetles belonging to the family Anthribidae .
Lumpsuckers or lumpfish are mostly small scorpaeniform marine fish of the family Cyclopteridae .
Agilisaurus ( /ˌædʒɨlɨˈsɔrəs/ ; ' agile lizard ' ) is a genus of ornithischian dinosaur from the Middle Jurassic Period of what is now eastern Asia .
Hieracium albertinum , known as western hawkweed or houndstongue hawkweed , is a species of the Hieracium genus that is very similar to Hieracium albiflorum with white flowers but differs in that the flower heads are clustered and the leaves , stems and bracts are covered in a thick layer of hairs .
The Baja California rainbow trout or San Pedro Martir trout or Nelson 's trout ( Oncorhynchus mykiss nelsoni ) is a localized subspecies of the rainbow trout ( Oncorhynchus mykiss ) , a fish in the Salmonidae family .
Aetapcus maculatus , the Warty prowfish , is a species of Australian prowfish endemic to the coastal waters of southern Australia where it inhabits mostly rocky reefs .
Neocyclotidae is a family of tropical land snails with gills and an operculum , terrestrial gastropod mollusks in the informal group Architaenioglossa belonging to the clade Caenogastropoda ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
Aspidophoroides is a genus of poachers native to the northern Pacific and Atlantic oceans .
Pardosa maisa is a wolf spider species in the genus Pardosa found in Finland , Austria , Hungary , Czech Republic , Poland and Russia .
Neolepetopsidae is a family of small deep sea sea snails or true limpets , marine gastropod mollusks in the clade Patellogastropoda ( according to the taxonomy of the Gastropoda by Bouchet & Rocroi , 2005 ) .
The Pyrgotidae are an unusual family of flies ( Diptera ) , one of only two families of Cyclorrhapha that lack ocelli .
Apiopetalum velutinum is a species of plant in the Mackinlayaceae family .
Ameles gracilis is a species of praying mantis found on the Canary Islands .
Tetrabaena socialis is a microscopic species of green algae and one of the simplest multicellular organism , consisting of four cells .
Haliotis cyclobates , common name the whirling abalone or the circular ear shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Haliotidae , the abalones .
Passiflora edulis is a vine species of passion flower that is native to Brazil , Paraguay and northern Argentina .
Squaliobarbus curriculus , the Barbel chub , is a species of cyprinid fish that is found in China , North Korea , South Korea , eastern Russia and Vietnam .
Zygoballus rufipes , commonly called the hammerjawed jumper , is a species of jumping spider which occurs in the United States , Canada , and Central America .
Adiantum edgeworthii is a species of ferns in the Vittarioideae subfamily of the Pteridaceae .
Juncus conglomeratus , known commonly as Compact Rush , is a perennial , herbaceous flowering plant species in the rush family Juncaceae .
Eutaxia diffusa , commonly known as Spreading Eutaxia , is a shrub species in the Fabaceae family .
Dichochrysa pilinota is a species of green lacewing .
Phrynops tuberosus , commonly known as the Cotinga River toadhead turtle , is a large species endemic to South America .
Cyathea gleichenioides is a species of tree fern endemic to New Guinea , where it grows in open peaty grassland and on forest margins , often in groups , at an altitude of 2800 - -3700 m. The trunk of this plant is erect , up to 3 m tall and about 24 cm in diameter .
Monothrix polylepis , the Littoral cusk , is a species of viviparous brotula known from shallow reefs off the coast of eastern Australia .
Apocorophium is a genus of amphipod crustaceans , comprising the following species :
Polygonum patulum , called tree hogweed , is a species of flowering plant in the knotweed family .
Agathosma gonaquensis ( the Gonaqua Buchu ) is a species of plant in the family Rutaceae .
Sicyopterus franouxi is a species of goby endemic to Madagascar where it is only found in fresh waters .
Conopea is a genus of barnacle , containing the following species :
Cellana ornata is a species of true limpet , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Nacellidae , one of the families of true limpets .
Sulfitobacter brevis is a species of bacteria isolated from the hypersaline , heliothermal and meromictic Antarctic Ekho Lake .
Phrynopus is a genus of frogs of the Craugastoridae family .
Allium cassium is a Middle Eastern species of wild onion native to Turkey , Lebanon , Israel , and Cyprus .
Commidendrum is a genus of trees and shrubs in the sunflower family endemic to the island of Saint Helena in the South Atlantic Ocean .
Ectillaenus is a genus of trilobites in the order Corynexochida .
Mazus gracilis is a plant species native to the Provinces of Henan , Hubei , Jiangsu , Jiangxi and Zhejiang in China .
Semionotus ( `` Flag - Back '' ) is an extinct genus of ray - finned fish found throughout Northern Pangaea ( North America and Europe ) during the late Triassic , becoming extinct in the Early Jurassic .
Aberlemnia is a genus of extinct vascular plants of the Early Devonian ( around 420 to 390 million years ago ) , which consisted of leafless stems with terminal spore - forming organs ( sporangia ) .
Parashorea densiflora ( also called White Seraya ) is a species of plant in the family Dipterocarpaceae .
Spiraviridae is a family of single stranded DNA viruses that infect archeae .
Kalanchoe brasiliensis , the folha da fortuna , saião , folha da costa or coerama , is a plant species in the genus Kalanchoe .
Isachne is a widespread genus of tropical and subtropical plants in the grass family , found in Asia , Africa , Australia , the Americas , and various oceanic islands .
Cylindrolobus cootesii ( Cootes ' Cylindrolobus ) is plant species of the family Orchidaceae endemic to the Philippines .
The Guadalupe spiny softshell turtle ( Apalone spinifera guadalupensis ) is a subspecies of soft - shelled turtle native to the United States , in the state of Texas .
Cyperus ustulatus , also known as giant umbrella - sedge or coastal cutty grass is a species of sedge native to New Zealand .
Spaniacris deserticola is a species of insect in family Acrididae known by the common name Coachella Valley grasshopper .
Hemifusus ternatanus , common name Ternate False Fusus , is a species of sea snails , marine gastropod mollusks in the family Melongenidae , the crown conches and their allies .
Philcoxia bahiensis is a rare plant species in the Plantaginaceae that is endemic to the Brazilian state of Bahia .
Parazumia is a neotropical and nearctic genus of medium to large sized potter wasps .
Dicranum scoparium , the broom forkmoss , is a species of dicranid moss , native to North America , including the Great Lakes region .
Geopinus incrassatus is a species of beetle in the family Carabidae , the only species in the genus Geopinus .
Silphium mohrii , known by the common names Mohr 's rosinweed and shaggy rosinweed , is a species of flowering plant in the Composite family .
E. bulbosa is the only species in the genus Erigenia ( Nutt . )
Notocetichthys trunovi , Trunov 's southern cetomimid , is a species of flabby whalefish only known from the Lazarev Sea near Antarctica where it is found at depths of from 1,210 to 1,360 metres ( 3,970 to 4,460 ft ) .
Jaggermeryx is an extinct genus of semiaquatic anthracothere , ungulates related to hippopotamuses , from early Miocene Africa .
Bromus diandrus is a species of grass known by the common names great brome and `` ripgut brome '' .
Patsuia is a butterfly genus of the Limenitidinae . The genus is confined to West China and Tibet .
Zoobotryon verticillatum , commonly known as the spaghetti bryozoan , is a species of colonial bryozoan with a bush - like structure .
Eriogonum arborescens is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name Santa Cruz Island buckwheat .
Copelatus amaroides is a species diving beetle .
Juniperus taxifolia ( Bonin Islands juniper ; Japanese : シマムロ Shimamuro ) is a species of juniper , endemic to the Bonin Islands southeast of Japan .
Limneria insculpta is a species of small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Velutinidae .
The Beldaco ( Pseudobombax millei ) is a species of flowering plant in the Malvaceae family .
Anomoiodon is an extinct genus of procolophonine procolophonid parareptile from early Triassic deposits of Thuringia , Germany .
Clepsigenes dissota is a moth in the Xyloryctidae family , and the only species in the genus Clepsigenes .
Brookesia is a genus of chameleons endemic to Madagascar , that range from small to very small in size , and are known collectively as leaf chameleons ( though this name also commonly is used for species in the genera Rieppeleon and Rhampholeon ) .
Anacyclus is a genus of plants in the Asteraceae family described by Linnaeus in 1753 .
Latiaxis lischkeanus is a species of medium - sized sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the subfamily Coralliophilinae of the family Muricidae .
Platanthera algeriensis is a species of orchid native to eastern and southeastern Spain , Corsica , Sardinia , Algeria and Morocco .
Carex capitata is a species of sedge known by the common name capitate sedge .
Dipteridae is an extinct family of prehistoric lungfishes which lived during the Devonian period .
Bathycrinidae is a family of echinoderms in the class Crinoidea .
Indoxysticus is a small genus of crab spiders , native to Asia .
Neocaridina is a genus of atyid shrimp , containing the following species :
Streptomyces hirsutus is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which has been isolated from soil in Switzerland .
The Zygaenoidea comprise the superfamily of moths that includes burnet moths , forester moths , and relatives .
Francisella is a genus of pathogenic , Gram - negative bacteria .
Allium is a genus of monocotyledonous flowering plants that includes the cultivated onion , garlic , scallion , shallot and leek as well as chives and hundreds of other wild species .
Evergestis subfuscalis is a species of moth in the Crambidae family .
Symphyotrichum dumosum , common names rice button aster or bushy aster , is a plant species long known as Aster dumosus .
Chelidonichthys obscurus , the Longfin gurnard , is a species of sea robin that can be found in such seas as Aegean and Black Seas and from British Isles to Mauritania .
Aerangis ugandensis is a species of epiphytic orchid native to Uganda , Kenya , Rwanda , Burundi , and Congo - Kinshasa ( Zaire , Democratic Republic of the Congo ) .
Rubus insulanus is a North American species of flowering plants in the rose family .
Cottunculus is a genus of fatheads found in the Atlantic , Pacific and Arctic oceans .
Pleurobranchaea maculata , or the grey side - gilled slug , is a species of sea slug , specifically a side - gill slug or notaspidean .
Ilex amelanchier , the swamp holly or sarvis holly , is a rare species of holly from the southeastern United States .
Pupilla blandi , common name the Rocky Mountain column , is a species of very small or minute air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial pulmonate gastropod mollusk or micromollusk in the family Pupillidae .
Pinus yunnanensis , the Yunnan pine , is a species of conifer in the Pinaceae family .
Carex subnigricans is a species of sedge known by the common name nearlyblack sedge .
Parablabicentrus angustatus is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Parablabicentrus .
Crepis setosa , the bristly hawksbeard , is a European species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
Eustenopus villosus is a species of true weevil known as the yellow starthistle hairy weevil .
Dorylus , also known as driver ants , safari ants , or siafu , is a large genus of army ants found primarily in central and east Africa , although the range also extends to tropical Asia .
Thymus praecox is a species of thyme .
Santolina is a genus of plants in the chamomile tribe within the sunflower family , primarily from the western Mediterranean region .
Imeroherpiidae is a family of solenogaster , comprising the sole genus Imeroherpia .
Typhochlaena curumim is a species of tarantula , that is native to `` Mata do Pau - Ferro '' , Areia , in the state of Paraiba , Brazil .
Myrmecia nigriceps , also known as the black - headed bull ant , is a species of ant endemic to Australia .
Calocoris affinis is a species of bug in the subfamily Mirinae of the family Miridae that can be found everywhere in Europe except for Switzerland and Greece .
Stefania ginesi ( tepuis treefrog , Spanish : rana stefania del Hermano Gines ) is a species of frog in the family Hemiphractidae .
Tilia chinensis ( Chinese linden , Chinese : 椴树 ) is a species of lime or linden tree that is endemic to China .
Pseudothyestes flavolineata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Pseudothyestes .
Dactyloscopus metoecus , the Mexican stargazer , is a species of sand stargazer native to the Pacific coast of Mexico where it can be found at depths of from 0 to 7 metres ( 0 to 23 ft ) .
Stenella gynoxidicola , formerly Cladosporium gynoxidicola is a species of anamorphic fungi .
Cinysca alvesi is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Areneidae .
Hieracium murorum , wall hawkweed is a species of flowering plant in the sunflower family .
Jugumella is a genus of extinct plants of the Late Silurian ( Přídolí , around 430 to 420 million years ago ) .
Thyridolepis is a genus of Australian plants in the grass family .
Glirodon is a genus of extinct mammal from the Upper Jurassic .
Allium flavovirens is a species of onions endemic to the western part of Inner Mongolia .
Deroceras tarracense is a species of terrestrial slug in the family Agriolimacidae .
Honora perdubiella is a species of snout moth in the genus Honora .
The only species of this genus is Doloma leucocephala Prout , 1922 .
Toxorhynchites rajah is a species of mosquito in the genus Toxorhynchites .
It consists of only one species , Tossea setosa , which is found in Ecuador ( Pichincha Province ) .
Rubus illecebrosus is a red - fruited species of Rubus that originally came from Japan , but is also very popular in some European countries like Lithuania .
Catalpa speciosa , commonly known as the northern catalpa , hardy catalpa , western catalpa , cigar tree , and catawba - tree , is a species of Catalpa native to the midwestern United States .
Sparganium eurycarpum is a species of bur - reed known by the common names broadfruit bur - reed and giant bur - reed .
The harvester termites are an ancient , Old World family of termites , Hodotermitidae .
Keteleeria evelyniana ( Evelyn keteleeria , Chinese : 云南油杉 ; pinyin : Yúnnán yóushān , Vietnamese : Du sam ) is a species of conifer native to southern China , Laos and Vietnam .
Monardella follettii is an uncommon species of flowering plant in the mint family known by the common name Follett 's monardella .
The Mastophoroideae are a subfamily of Corallinaceaen Coralline alga with uniporate conceptacles .
Cambaroides is a genus of freshwater crayfish .
Packera werneriifolia , known by the common names alpine rock butterweed and hoary groundsel , is a species of flowering plant in the aster family .
Neowerdermannia is a genus of South American cacti .
The only known species is Petrobium arboreum , called Saint Helena Whitewood .
Paracarcinosoma is a genus of carcinosomatid eurypterid .
Raorchestes annandalii ( known also as Annandale 's bush frog , Himalaya bubble - nest frog , or Himalaya foam nest frog ) is a species of frog in the Rhacophoridae family .
Qatrania is an extinct genus of primates .
Pelomyxa is a genus of giant flagellar amoeboid protists , usually 500 - 800 μm but occasionally up to 5 mm in length , found in anaerobic or microaerobic bottom sediments of stagnant freshwater ponds or slow - moving streams .
Oncotylus pyrethri is a species of plant bugs belonging to the family Miridae , subfamily Phylinae that is found in Russia and Ukraine .
The Sironidae are a family of harvestmen with more than 30 described species .
Haigia diegensis is a species of ulidiid or picture - winged fly in the genus Haigia of the family Ulidiidae .
Urtica is a genus of flowering plants in the family Urticaceae .
Pella carolina is a species of rove beetle in the genus Pella in the subfamily Aleocharinae .
Paraclinus grandicomis , the Horned blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny native to reefs of the Atlantic Ocean and the Caribbean Sea from southern Florida through the Lesser Antilles .
Eleocharis rostellata is a species of spikesedge known by the common name beaked spikerush .
Neofibularia nolitangere , the touch - me - not sponge , is a species of demosponge in the family Desmacellidae .
Balaustium cristatum is a species of mite belonging to the family Erythraeidae .
The Talas tuco - tuco ( Ctenomys talarum ) is a species of tuco - tuco endemic to eastern Argentina .
Megalobulimus paranaguensis is a species of air - breathing land snail , a terrestrial gastropod mollusk in the family Strophocheilidae .
Chereas octomaculata is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Chereas .
Euryomma peregrinum is a small species of fly from the family Fanniidae .
The Siberian tiger ( Panthera tigris altaica ) , also known as the Amur tiger , is a tiger subspecies inhabiting mainly the Sikhote Alin mountain region with a small population in southwest Primorye Province in the Russian Far East .
Neoschumannia is a genus of plant in family Apocynaceae , first described as a genus in 1905 .
Elophila minoralis is a species of moth of the Crambidae family that is found in Madagascar .
Streptomyces atrovirens is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which was isolated from soil in Egypt .
Belonimorphis belonimorphis is a species of very small sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Cerithiopsidae .
Oedipoda germanica , the ' Red - winged Grasshopper ' , is a species of ' short - horned grasshoppers ' belonging to the family Acrididae subfamily Oedipodinae .
Coptotermes elisae , the Papuan plantation termite , is a species of termite in the family Rhinotermitidae .
Vermilacinia howei is classified in the subgenus Cylindricaria in which it is distinguished from related species by the thallus divided into tubular slightly inflated branches .
Sybroplocia sybroides is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Sybroplocia .
Zostera nigricaulis is a species of eelgrass native to the seacoasts of New South Wales , Victoria , South Australia , Western Australia and Tasmania .
Crepidodera peloponnesiaca is a species of flea beetle from Chrysomelidae family that is endemic to Greece .
Bonapartenykus ( named in honor of José Bonaparte ) is a genus of alvarezsaurid theropod dinosaurs known from the Late Cretaceous ( Campanian / Maastrichtian stage ) of northwestern Patagonia , Argentina .
Hybomitra aterrima is a species of horse fly in the family Tabanidae .
Cebrennus is a genus of huntsman spiders mostly found in Northern Africa and the Arabian Peninsula .
The Vanuatu megapode or Vanuatu scrubfowl ( Megapodius layardi ) is a species of bird in the Megapodiidae family .
Tectaria is a genus of fern in the family Tectariaceae .
Calamagrostis rubescens is a species of grass known by the common name pinegrass .
Oncidium ensatum , Latin American orchid , is a species of orchid found from southern Florida , southern Mexico ( Chiapas + the Yucatán Peninsula ) , Central America , Cuba , the Bahamas , and northwestern Venezuela .
Congiopodidae is a family of scorpaeniform fishes native to the southern hemisphere , commonly known as pigfishes , horsefishes and racehorses .
Hieracium pilosella ( syn . Pilosella officinarum ) , known as mouseear hawkweed , is a yellow - flowered species of flowering plant in the daisy family Asteraceae , native to Europe and northern Asia .
