Glandularia pulchella is a species of flowering plant in the verbena family known by the common name South American mock vervain .
Hoplocorypha brevicollis is a species of praying mantis found in South Africa .
Omphaliodes obscura is a species of moth of the Anthelidae family , and the only species in the genus Omphaliodes .
Amoria zebra , common name the zebra volute , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Volutidae , the volutes .
Chlorolestes elegans is a species of damselfly in the family Synlestidae .
Tayloria nepalensis is an extant dung moss species found in Nepal .
Buddleja scordioides is endemic to central Arizona , southeastern New Mexico , southwestern Texas , and the Chihuahua Desert of Mexico , growing amidst xeric thorn - scrub on alkaline soils at elevations of 600 -- 2,500 m. The species was first named and described by Kunth in 1818 .
Tephritis neesii is a species of fly found across Europe .
Bidens leptocephala ( fewflower beggarticks ) is a North American species of flowering plant in the daisy family .
Aquilegia grahamii is a species of flowering plant in the buttercup family known by the common name Graham 's columbine .
Boidae ( Common names : boas , boids , boioids ) is a family of nonvenomous snakes found in America , Africa , Europe , Asia , and some Pacific Islands .
Parviturbo fenestratus is a species of a rare , minute sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Skeneidae .
Diplostomatidae is a family of trematodes in the order Strigeidida .
Veyretella is a genus of terrestrial flowering plants in the orchid family , Orchidaceae .
Allorchestes compressa is a species of amphipod in the family Dogielinotidae .
Mahé day gecko ( Phelsuma sundbergi longinsulae Rendahl , 1939 ( syn . Phelsuma longinsulae pulchra Rendahl , 1939 ) ) is a diurnal subspecies of geckos .
Bathylaco is a genus of slickheads found in deep oceanic waters .
Tonyosynthemis ofarrelli , more commonly known as the slender tigertail , is a species of Odonata from the family Synthemistidae originating from eastern Queensland , Australia , found along the eastern coast .
Oreoxis humilis is a rare species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common name Rocky Mountain alpineparsley .
Brotulinella taiwanensis , the Taiwan coral - brotula , is a species of viviparous brotula , the only known member of its genus , found mostly in the surge zone of the waters around Taiwan and the Philippines where it lives amongst rocks .
Pittosporum eugenioides , common names lemonwood or tarata , is a species of New Zealand native tree .
Agyneta galapagosensis is a species of sheet weaver found in the Galápagos Islands and Brazil .
Bidens tripartita is a common and widespread species of plants in the sunflower family , commonly known as Three - lobe Beggarticks , Three - part Beggarticks , Leafy - bracted Beggarticks or Trifid Bur - marigold .
Canthigaster is a genus in the pufferfish family ( Tetraodontidae ) .
Cornus unalaschkensis is a species of flowering plant in the Cornaceae , the dogwood family .
The Brazilian tinamou is a monotypic species .
Enchelyurus kraussii , Krauss ' blenny , is a species of combtooth blenny found in coral reefs in the western Pacific and Indian Oceans .
Paphiopedilum barbigerum is a species of flowering plant in the family Orchidaceae known commonly as the beard carrying paphiopedilum .
Callicarpa reevesii is a species of beautyberry native to Brazil that is a small shrub .
Sibbaldiopsis is a genus in the plant family Rosaceae containing the single species Sibbaldiopsis tridentata .
Vermivora is a genus of New World warblers .
Egletes viscosa ( erect tropical daisy ) is a New World species of flowering plant in the sunflower family .
Ichnanthus , commonly called bedgrass , is a genus of tropical plants in the grass family , widespread in Africa , Asia , Australia , and the Americas .
Yunia is a genus of extinct vascular plants from the Early Devonian ( Pragian or Siegenian stage , around 411 to 408 million years ago ) .
Fagraea gracilipes is a species of flowering plant in the family Gentianaceae .
Oxygonia annulipes is a beetle species from the family of ground beetles ( Carabidae ) .
It contains only one species , Philagraulella punica , which is found in Sudan .
Acmella nana is a species of land snail discovered from Borneo , Malaysia , in 2015 .
Alzoniella pellitica is a species of very small aquatic snail , a spring snail , an operculate gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae .
Antennaria luzuloides is a North American species of flowering plants in the daisy family known by the common name rush pussytoes .
Robiquetia succisa is a species of orchid occurring from the eastern Himalaya to southern China and Indochina .
Acropora horrida is a species of acroporid coral that was first described by James Dwight Dana in 1846 .
Nesoluma polynesicum , the keahi or island nesoluma , is a species of flowering plant in the chicle family , Sapotaceae .
The Rhodospirillales are an order of Proteobacteria , with two families : the Acetobacteraceae and the Rhodospirillaceae .
Gymnocranius euanus , the Japanese large - eye bream , is a species of emperor native to the Indo Pacific found at depths of 15 to 50 meters .
Macromia illinoiensis , also known as the swift river cruiser or the Illinois river cruiser , is a species of dragonfly in the Macromiidae family .
The Central American mud turtle ( Kinosternon angustipons ) , also known as the narrow - bridged mud turtle , is a species of mud turtle in the Kinosternidae family endemic to Central America .
Amphobotrys ricini is a species of fungus in the family Sclerotiniaceae .
Brickellia scoparia is a Mesoamerican species of flowering plants in the daisy family .
Oreonectes retrodorsalis is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Oreonectes .
Heniartes is a large genus of assassin bugs belonging to the family Reduviidae ; 32 species have been described , all from South America .
Allium serra is a California species of wild onion known by several common names , including jeweled onion , pom - pon onion , and serrated onion .
Clarkia prostrata is a species of flowering plant in the evening primrose family known by the common name prostrate clarkia .
Centrochir crocodili is the only species in the genus Centrochir of the catfish ( order Siluriformes ) family Doradidae .
Felis chaus maimanah is considered a subspecies of the jungle cat .
Cremnoconchus syhadrensis is a species of freshwater snail , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Littorinidae , the winkles or periwinkles .
Cyathea brooksii is a species of tree fern native to Cuba , Hispaniola and Puerto Rico , where it grows on serpentine soils in shaded ravines , along streams , and on forested slopese at an altitude of 250 - 950 m. The trunk is prostrate and only about 6 cm in diameter .
Ergasilus is a genus of copepod crustaceans occurring in both the ocean and fresh water , often called gill lice .
Cnemaspis clivicola , is a species of diurnal gecko endemic to island of Sri Lanka .
Guadua is a Neotropical genus of thorny , clumping bamboo in the grass family , ranging from moderate to very large species .
Prince Demidoff 's bushbaby ( Galagoides demidovii ) , also known as Prince Demidoff 's galago , is a species of primate in the Galagidae Family .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Grimmicola parasiticus .
Velodona togata is a species of octopus in the monotypic genus Velodona .
Tabanus bovinus , sometimes called the pale giant horse - fly , is a species of biting horse - fly .
Hesperevax acaulis is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name stemless dwarf cudweed .
Austrocochlea constricta , common name the common periwinkle , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Dianthus nardiformis or Dianthus gelidus is a species of herbaceous perennial plant in the genus Dianthus .
Thililua is a genus of polycotylid plesiosaur , containing one species , T. longicollis .
Alcidion umbraticum is a species of longhorn beetles of the subfamily Lamiinae , and the only species in the genus Alcidion .
Some experts demote Galeaspida to the rank of subclass , and unite it with Pituriaspida and Osteostraci to form the class Monorhina .
Cymbolaena is a monotypic genus of flowering plants in the aster family , Asteraceae , containing the single species Cymbolaena griffithii .
Brachauchenius ( meaning ' short neck ' ) is an extinct genus of pliosaurid that lived in America ( USA and Colombia ) during the Cretaceous .
Eunicella verrucosa , the broad sea fan , pink sea fan or warty gorgonian , is a species of colonial Gorgonian `` soft coral '' in the Gorgoniidae family .
Itaboravis is an extinct genus of land bird uncovered from the Late Paleocene of São José do Itaboraí , Rio de Janeiro state , Brazil .
Hallucigenia is a genus of Cambrian animals known from articulated fossils in Burgess Shale - type deposits in Canada and China , and from isolated spines around the world .
Leptomenes is a genus of potter wasps found in the African and Palearctic regions known to dig itself into the flesh of an animal .
Solva marginata also known as the drab wood - soldierfly is a species of soldier fly in the family Xylomyidae , the `` wood soldier flies '' .
Homarus morrisi is a species of fossil lobster from the Eocene of southern England .
The sand leek ( Allium scorodoprasum ) , also known as rocambole , is a Eurasian species of wild onion with a native range extending across much of Europe and the Middle East .
Woodwardia radicans ( common names chain fern , European chain fern and rooting chainfern ) is a species of fern in the family Blechnaceae , native to the Atlantic islands and southwestern Europe .
Phymatosorus scolopendria commonly called monarch fern , musk fern , maile - scented fern , lauaʻe or wart fern is a species of fern within the Polypodiaceae family .
Origanum is a genus of herbaceous perennials and subshrubs in the family Lamiaceae , native to Europe , North Africa , and much of temperate Asia , where they are found in open or mountainous habitats .
Wonambi is a genus that consisted of two species of very large snakes .
Emeroleter is an extinct genus of nycteroleterid parareptile known from the early Late Permian of European Russia .
Arceuthobium divaricatum is a species of dwarf mistletoe known as pinyon dwarf mistletoe .
Neocollyris rugei is a species of ground beetle in the genus Neocollyris in the subfamily Carabinae .
Chiloglanis congicus is a species of upside - down catfish endemic to the Democratic Republic of the Congo where it occurs in the lower Congo River basin .
Badisis is a stilt - legged fly genus with only one known species , Badisis ambulans .
Neuburgia macroloba is a species of flowering plant in the family Loganiaceae .
Carex toreadora is a little - known species of sedge from Ecuador .
This is a monotypic genus , containing the single species Panorbis viscosus .
Dolabrifera dolabrifera is a species of sea hare , a marine gastropod mollusc in the family Aplysiidae , the sea hares .
Strongylosteus hindenburgi is an extinct genus of prehistoric bony fish that lived during the early Toarcian stage of the Early Jurassic epoch .
Spectracanthicus is a genus of suckermouth armored catfishs endemic to Brazil .
Baluchicardia is an extinct genus of fossil saltwater clams , marine bivalve molluscs in the family Carditidae .
Eriogonum reniforme is a species of wild buckwheat known by the common name kidney - leaf buckwheat .
Eleutherodactylus leberi is a species of frog in the Eleutherodactylidae family , endemic to Cuba .
Streptomyces capillispiralis is a bacterium species from the genus of Streptomyces which was isolated from soil in Sweden .
Oxyria digyna ( mountain sorrel , wood sorrel , Alpine sorrel or Alpine mountain - sorrel ) is a species of flowering plant in the Buckwheat Family ( Polygonaceae ) .
Nurscia is a genus of spiders in the family Titanoecidae .
Erythrodes ( false helmetorchid ) is a genus of flowering plants from the orchid family , Orchidaceae .
Notropis wickliffi ( channel shiner ) is a species of ray - finned fish in the genus Notropis .
Tachymarptis is a genus of bird in the swift family , Apodidae .
It contains the single species Diaxanthia lucinia , which is found in Costa Rica .
Archaeorhizomyces finlayi is a species of fungi in the class Archaeorhizomycetes and the type species .
Trichopilia brasiliensis is a species of orchid endemic to Brazil ( Goiás ) .
Assiminea mesopotamica is a species of minute , salt - tolerant snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusks , or micromollusks , in the family Assimineidae .
Davallia fejeensis is a species of fern in the Davalliaceae family .
Micromoema xiphophora is a species of rivuline endemic to the Orinoco River basin in Venezuela where it is found in small pools in the forest .
Hemileiocassis panjang is a species of bagrid catfish endemic to Indonesia .
Thalotia chlorostoma , common name the greem - mouth monodont , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Trochidae , the top snails .
Glaciecola punicea is a psychrophilic bacteria found in Antarctic sea - ice habitats , being the type species of its genus .
The genus itself contains only one species , Telechrysis tripuncta , which is found in most of Europe , except the Iberian Peninsula , the Benelux , Ireland , Lithuania , Croatia , Austria and Greece .
Phaeosaccion is a genus of brown algae with monostromatic tubular to saccate thalli , up to 20 centimetres ( 7.9 in ) long and to 2 centimetres ( 0.79 in ) wide .
Atalaya calcicola is a species of trees native to Northern and Eastern Queensland .
Biscogniauxia capnodes a species of fungus in the family Xylariaceae . It is a plant pathogen .
Nassella ( needlegrass ) is a New World genus of over 100 perennial bunchgrasses found from North America through South America .
Memecylon royenii is a species of plant in the Melastomataceae family endemic to Sri Lanka .
Spiraea chamaedryfolia , common name germander meadowsweet or elm - leaved spirea , is a species of plants belonging to the family Rosaceae .
Monochilus is a genus of plants in the mint family , Lamiaceae , first described in 1835 .
Huxleyia habooba is a species of small , monomyarian , nuculoid bivalve .
Epiphyllum anguliger , commonly known as the fishbone cactus , is a cactus species native to Mexico .
Chrysosplenium alternifolium is a species of flowering plant in the saxifrage family known as the alternate - leaved golden - saxifrage .
Xenotilapia ochrogenys is a species of cichlid endemic to Lake Tanganyika where it prefers areas with sandy substrates .
Pterocoma is an extinct genus of crinoid from the Late Jurassic of Europe .
Boerhavia dominii , commonly known as tarvine , is a species of flowering plant in the four o'clock family .
Azadinium spinosum is a species of dinoflagellate that produces azaspiracid toxins ( toxins associated with shellfish poisoning ) , particularly AZA 1 , AZA 2 and an isomer of AZA 2 .
Puccinellia maritima is a species of grass known by the common names including seaside alkaligrass , common saltmarsh - grass or sea poa grass .
Thamnomanes is a genus of antshrikes in the perching bird family Thamnophilidae .
Paramimiculus pterolophioides is a species of beetle in the family Cerambycidae , and the only species in the genus Paramimiculus .
Heliangelus is a genus of hummingbirds found in montane South America .
Floscaldasia is a genus of South American flowering plant in the sunflower family .
Pseudocheirodon is a genus of characins found in southern Central America .
The type species is Pterofiltrus qiui .
Arctocephalus forsteri , the New Zealand fur seal , southern fur seal or long - nosed fur seal , is a species of fur seal found around the south coast of Australia , the coast of the South Island of New Zealand , and some of the small islands to the south and east of there .
Cochlicella barbara is a species of small but very high - spired , air - breathing land snail , a pulmonate gastropod mollusk in the family Cochlicellidae .
Posidonichthys hutchinsi is a species of clingfish native to the Australia coast .
Desmodus draculae is an extinct species of vampire bat that inhabited South America during the Pleistocene , and possibly the early Holocene .
Ostrea edulis is a species of oyster native to Europe and commonly known as the European flat oyster , Colchester native oyster ( hence Colchester natives ) , mud oyster , or edible oyster ( despite this latter name it is not the only oyster that is edible by humans ) .
Cirsonella weldii , common name the shiny liotia , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Skeneidae .
The rose subfamily Rosoideae consists of more than 850 species , including many shrubs , perennial herbs , and fruit plants such as strawberries and brambles .
The Didelphinae are a subfamily of opossums consisting of 15 genera and 98 species , one of them extinct .
Banksia nutans , commonly known as Nodding Banksia , is a species of shrub native to the south coast of Western Australia in the genus Banksia .
There is only one known species , Melasphaerula graminea , native to Namibia and the Cape Province in South Africa .
Paraclinus nigripinnis , the Blackfin blenny , is a species of labrisomid blenny native to the western Atlantic Ocean and the Caribbean Sea from southern Florida to Brazil .
Orobanche ramosa is a species of broomrape known by the common names hemp broomrape and branched broomrape .
Senecio nigrescens is a species of the genus Senecio and family Asteraceae and was first written about in the botanical classic Botany of Beechey 's Voyage to the Pacific and Behring 's Straits .
Ceratozamia hildae , commonly known as the bamboo cycad , is a species of cycad in the Zamiaceae family that is endemic to Mexico .
Callicarpa bodinieri ( Bodinier 's beautyberry ) is a species of flowering plant in the genus Callicarpa of the family Lamiaceae , native to West and Central China .
Chaenactis furcata is a Mexican species of flowering plants in the aster family .
The Nullarbor dwarf bettong ( Bettongia pusilla ) was a species of bettong endemic to the Nullarbor Plain in Western Australia .
Terestrombus terebellatus , common name : the Little Auger Conch , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Strombidae , the true conchs .
Acrantophis madagascariensis is a species of boid snake in the subfamily Sanziniinae that is endemic to the island of Madagascar .
Mene oblonga is a species of perciform fish that first appeared in the Monte Bolca Lagerstatten during the Lutetian epoch of the Eocene .
Perideridia kelloggii is a species of flowering plant in the carrot family known by the common name Kellogg 's yampah .
Trichomycterus punctulatus is a species of fish of the family Trichomycteridae in the order of the Siluriformes .
Myoictis is a genus of marsupials in the order Dasyuromorphia .
Etheostoma variatum ( common name variegate darter ) is a species of darter .
Calliostoma zietzi , common name the Zietz top shell , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Calliostomatidae .
Candida viswanathii is a species of yeast in the genus Candida .
Phaseolus ( bean , wild bean ) is a genus in the family Fabaceae containing about 70 plant species , all native to the Americas , primarily Mexico .
Zygoballus iridescens is a species of jumping spider which occurs in the United States .
Tabebuia elliptica is a species of Tabebuia tree native to Brazil and Bolivia .
Ranularia exilis , common name : the slender triton , is a species of predatory sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Ranellidae , the triton snails , triton shells or tritons .
Tetragraptus approximatus is a species of dichograptid graptolite belonging to the genus Tetragraptus .
The Prodoxidae are a family of moths , generally small in size and nondescript in appearance .
Allium funckiifolium is a plant species from Hubei and Sichuan Provinces in China .
Falniowskia neglectissima is a species of freshwater snail with an operculum , an aquatic gastropod mollusk in the family Hydrobiidae , the snouted freshwater snails .
Ecsenius lineatus , known commonly as the Linear blenny or Lined combtooth blenny , is a species of marine fish in the family Blenniidae .
Vericeras is an extinct genus of actively mobile carnivorous cephalopod , essentially a Nautiloid , that lived in what would be Europe during the Silurian from 421 - -418.7 mya , existing for approximately 2.3 million years .
Hildoceratidae is a family of ammonoid cephalopods from the Lower Jurassic , lower Pliensbachian ( Jamesoni zone ) to lower Bajocian ( maybe even upper Bajocian ) substages , generally with strongly ribbed , involute shells .
Ornithogalum dubium , common names sun star or star of Bethlehem , is a species of flowering plant in the family Asparagaceae , subfamily Scilloideae .
Furcifer is a genus of chameleons whose member species are mostly endemic to Madagascar , but F. cephalolepis and F. polleni are endemic to the Comoros .
Calamus elegans is a palm species in the genus Calamus .
Dictyna ignobilis is spider species found in Moldavia and Armenia .
Yohoia is a genus of tiny , extinct animals from the Cambrian period that has been found as fossils in the Burgess Shale formation of British Columbia , Canada .
Fissurella peruviana , common name : the Peruvian Keyhole Limpet , is a species of sea snail , a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Fissurellidae , the keyhole limpets .
Glossanodon is a genus of herring smelts .
Pentachaeta exilis is a species of flowering plant in the aster family known by the common name meager pygmydaisy .
Tibouchina pulchra is a plant species in the genus Tibouchina .
Amanita augusta is a species of agaric fungus in the family Amanitaceae .
Astacoides caldwelli is a species of crustacean in family Parastacidae .
Jensia is a genus of flowering plants in the daisy family , endemic to California .
It contains the single species Dacatria templaris , first described from South Korea .
Imocetus is an extinct genus of ziphiidae cetacean , with one species , G. piscatus , from the Miocene of Portugal and Spain .
Nannostomus marilynae , commonly known as Marilyn 's or greenstripe pencilfish , is a freshwater species of fish belonging to the Lebiasinidae family of characins .
Harpochloa is a genus of African plants in the grass family , common name caterpillar grass .
Xenisthmus chi ( Japan wriggler , chi xenisthmid ) is a species of fish in the wriggler family , Xenisthmidae .
Phlebodium is a small genus of two to four species of ferns , native to tropical and subtropical regions of the Americas .
Kentriodontidae is an extinct family of odontocet whales related to modern dolphins .
Syzygium cormiflorum , commonly known as the bumpy satinash , is a species of Syzygium tree native to Queensland in northeastern Australia .
Denticetopsis seducta is a species of whale catfish endemic to Brazil where it has a relatively wide , albeit scattered , distribution in the central and western portions of the Amazon basin and possibly the southwestern portions of the Orinoco River basin ; it is relatively disjunct from the other species of Denticetopsis .
Geocapromys is a genus of rodent , comprising two extant species of hutia .
Parodia columnaris is a species of cactus in the subfamily Cactoideae .
It contains only one species , Villarica villaricae , which is found in Chile ( Araucania Region ) .
Warszewitsch 's frog ( Rana warszewitschii ) is a species of frog in the Ranidae family found in Honduras , Nicaragua , Costa Rica , and Panama .
Callulina shengena is a species of frog in the family Brevicipitidae .
Annick Massis ( born 1 January 1958 ) is a French soprano .
Ivo Vinco ( 8 November 1927 -- 8 June 2014 ) was an Italian bass opera singer who enjoyed a successful international career .
Yelena Dudochkin is a Ukrainian - American soprano known for her `` gorgeous , expressive and rich voice ... a true pearl of the opera''(Voice of America ) and her `` dramatic intelligence '' ( Boston Globe ) .
Inva Mula ( born June 27 , 1963 ) is an Albanian opera lyric soprano .
Johann Carl Gottfried Loewe ( German : ( ˈløːvə ) ; 30 November 1796 -- 20 April 1869 ) , usually called Carl Loewe ( sometimes seen as Karl Loewe ) , was a German composer , tenor singer and conductor .
Eva Johansson ( 25 February 1958 ) is a Danish soprano opera singer .
Joseph Malovany(born in 1941 in Tel Aviv ) is an Israeli - born American tenor soloist .
Natale de Carolis ( born 25 July 1957 , Anagni ) is an Italian operatic baritone who has had an active career in major opera houses internationally since the early 1980s .
Jane Berbié ( born 6 May 1931 ) is a French mezzo - soprano particularly associated with Mozart and Rossini roles .
Albert Lortzing became an audience favourite , playing the roles of a youthful lover , a country boy and bon vivant , sometimes also singing small tenor or baritone roles .
